1
00:00:36,510 --> 00:00:39,280
(The last hurdle to the finals)

2
00:00:39,280 --> 00:00:40,647
What are they planning to do?

3
00:00:44,351 --> 00:00:47,455
(While everyone prepares
with their best efforts)

4
00:00:49,723 --> 00:00:51,392
(Milgari)

5
00:00:51,392 --> 00:00:53,361
(Milgari?)

6
00:00:53,361 --> 00:00:55,129
What is "Milgari?"

7
00:00:56,263 --> 00:00:57,464
Gumi's flour.

8
00:00:58,598 --> 00:01:00,801
Flour is called Milgari?

9
00:01:00,801 --> 00:01:04,071
It's Korean wheat.

10
00:01:04,071 --> 00:01:08,042
And since it was shipped as wheat
produced in Gumi,

11
00:01:08,042 --> 00:01:09,677
it came out labeled as "Milgari."

12
00:01:09,677 --> 00:01:11,177
It's a Gyeongsang-do dialect.

13
00:01:12,046 --> 00:01:15,082
The region I chose is Gumi,

14
00:01:15,082 --> 00:01:17,584
and the main ingredient is Milgari.

15
00:01:18,419 --> 00:01:21,087
Actually, calling that an ingredient
is a bit...

16
00:01:22,122 --> 00:01:23,356
Wheat flour?

17
00:01:24,225 --> 00:01:25,860
(Scratching head)

18
00:01:25,860 --> 00:01:27,294
That's quite difficult.

19
00:01:27,761 --> 00:01:30,996
Won't it be hard to show
something unique with that?

20
00:01:32,259 --> 00:01:35,495
(What kind of pastry will be made
with the ordinary ingredient "Milgari?")

21
00:01:37,004 --> 00:01:39,074
Since I've never been to Gumi,

22
00:01:39,074 --> 00:01:40,874
I researched a lot.

23
00:01:44,845 --> 00:01:48,115
(Milgari grown in fertile land
along the Nakdonggang River)

24
00:01:49,116 --> 00:01:52,186
In the case of Gumi Milgari,
there are no preservatives.

25
00:01:52,186 --> 00:01:55,856
Unlike imported wheat,
it was given to me fresh,

26
00:01:55,856 --> 00:01:59,459
so langue de chat was
the first thing that came to mind.

27
00:02:00,027 --> 00:02:02,062
- Langue de chat?
- Langue de chat.

28
00:02:02,896 --> 00:02:05,065
It translates to "cat's tongue."

29
00:02:05,065 --> 00:02:07,967
It means it's that thin.

30
00:02:07,967 --> 00:02:10,137
Didn't we eat Couque D'asse a lot
when we were kids?

31
00:02:10,371 --> 00:02:12,105
- Of course.
- I still eat Couque D'asse now.

32
00:02:12,105 --> 00:02:13,674
- It's the same.
- That's a langue de chat?

33
00:02:13,674 --> 00:02:15,142
(Understands immediately)

34
00:02:15,142 --> 00:02:17,645
I thought only the square ones
were langue de chat.

35
00:02:17,645 --> 00:02:19,936
(Currently producing them
in a square shape here)

36
00:02:20,481 --> 00:02:23,983
I've lived eating quite a lot until now.

37
00:02:24,316 --> 00:02:26,152
I make them a lot in France too.

38
00:02:27,254 --> 00:02:29,189
While being crispy...

39
00:02:29,657 --> 00:02:31,157
I want to pass this message along.

40
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:34,261
"She says it has to be crispy."

41
00:02:34,828 --> 00:02:35,896
"It has to be crispy."

42
00:02:35,896 --> 00:02:38,199
He's in trouble. It's an emergency.

43
00:02:42,870 --> 00:02:46,073
I think taking on a new challenge is
more meaningful to me.

44
00:02:51,679 --> 00:02:53,547
As for the pastry I made today,

45
00:02:53,547 --> 00:02:56,617
once you have one,
you won't be able to stop.

46
00:02:59,488 --> 00:03:01,188
- It's out.
- Langue de chat.

47
00:03:01,188 --> 00:03:03,190
(Langue de chat coming out golden brown)

48
00:03:06,718 --> 00:03:11,898
For langue de chat,
the Milgari is a fairly important point.

49
00:03:12,231 --> 00:03:14,101
(While preparing for the Round 4 mission)

50
00:03:14,101 --> 00:03:17,071
I kept making and discarding,
making and discarding.

51
00:03:17,805 --> 00:03:19,670
Even the ones I threw away,
if they seemed okay,

52
00:03:19,694 --> 00:03:21,108
I'd pick them up again,

53
00:03:21,108 --> 00:03:23,876
taste and compare them.

54
00:03:24,345 --> 00:03:27,180
I practiced so much
that it even appeared in my dreams.

55
00:03:27,748 --> 00:03:29,717
I wanted to make a pastry
that represents Gumi City.

56
00:03:29,717 --> 00:03:30,784
(The region's name is on the line.)

57
00:03:30,784 --> 00:03:33,021
The sub-ingredients I chose are...

58
00:03:33,021 --> 00:03:35,488
grapes and melon.

59
00:03:36,390 --> 00:03:38,592
He's cutting a melon.

60
00:03:38,859 --> 00:03:39,860
Melon?

61
00:03:40,628 --> 00:03:41,996
How will he use that?

62
00:03:41,996 --> 00:03:45,098
I know. It's difficult to bring out
the melon scent.

63
00:03:45,766 --> 00:03:48,381
Grapes and melon together?

64
00:03:48,405 --> 00:03:49,537
Melon and grapes.

65
00:03:49,537 --> 00:03:51,639
By making them into jam or cream?

66
00:03:51,639 --> 00:03:53,941
But it's not easy to bring out
the scent of those either.

67
00:03:53,941 --> 00:03:54,975
- The scent?
- Yes.

68
00:03:54,975 --> 00:03:56,076
Especially for melon.

69
00:03:56,311 --> 00:03:59,680
Among people in food marketing,

70
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:01,782
there are a few ingredients
they say you shouldn't use.

71
00:04:01,782 --> 00:04:05,186
Melon, Korean melon, watermelon,
and cucumber.

72
00:04:05,186 --> 00:04:07,522
That's right.
The scent people recognize and...

73
00:04:07,522 --> 00:04:09,188
the actual scent of the fruit
are different.

74
00:04:11,057 --> 00:04:14,161
(How will Yeong Seok bring out
the melon scent?)

75
00:04:15,963 --> 00:04:18,832
As soon as I thought of Gumi,
the idea that came to mind was...

76
00:04:19,193 --> 00:04:20,227
My Gummy.

77
00:04:22,436 --> 00:04:25,206
I thought, "What if I make a jelly gummy?"

78
00:04:26,507 --> 00:04:28,309
I thought using jelly to make it...

79
00:04:28,676 --> 00:04:31,979
would add another layer of fun.

80
00:04:36,884 --> 00:04:37,952
What is that?

81
00:04:37,952 --> 00:04:39,620
It looks like gelatin.

82
00:04:39,620 --> 00:04:42,756
I guess he's going to mix fruit
and gelatin to make a gummy.

83
00:04:43,324 --> 00:04:46,859
Grapes don't have a strong scent either.

84
00:04:46,859 --> 00:04:48,728
(They are fruits that are hard
to extract the scent from.)

85
00:04:49,830 --> 00:04:52,600
To preserve the natural taste
of the fruit,

86
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:55,903
I tried my best to extract the juice well.

87
00:04:57,105 --> 00:05:00,274
I tried straining it through a cloth
and grinding it.

88
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:02,076
By concentrating the scent,

89
00:05:02,076 --> 00:05:03,911
I tried to give it as much
of a highlight as possible.

90
00:05:03,911 --> 00:05:04,977
(Methods to concentrate the scent)

91
00:05:07,114 --> 00:05:10,251
I put in an immense amount of effort
to find the right texture.

92
00:05:10,985 --> 00:05:13,854
I went to ingredient stores
and bought every single variety,

93
00:05:13,854 --> 00:05:15,256
trying them one by one,

94
00:05:15,256 --> 00:05:18,359
checking the texture of each ingredient.

95
00:05:18,359 --> 00:05:21,094
(Grape and melon gummies completed
after a long texture quest)

96
00:05:23,163 --> 00:05:25,331
I'm curious to see how it turns out.

97
00:05:26,333 --> 00:05:29,803
I mixed Milgari and grapes
to make the layers,

98
00:05:29,803 --> 00:05:32,807
(Grape jelly on top
of the buttercream layer)

99
00:05:33,607 --> 00:05:36,110
For the other one,
I mixed Milgari and melon...

100
00:05:36,476 --> 00:05:37,711
to create the layers.

101
00:05:37,711 --> 00:05:40,813
(Melon jelly on top
of white chocolate ganache)

102
00:05:42,183 --> 00:05:46,019
I put in a lot of effort to make a pastry
that Gumi City can be proud of.

103
00:05:47,488 --> 00:05:50,323
If you visit Gumi and try my pastry,

104
00:05:50,524 --> 00:05:53,494
I think it might make you want
to come back to Gumi again.

105
00:05:54,728 --> 00:05:56,996
When we analyze big data,

106
00:05:57,164 --> 00:05:59,934
setting aside butter and milk,
the one that comes up most frequently...

107
00:05:59,934 --> 00:06:01,835
as a dessert ingredient is yuzu.

108
00:06:01,835 --> 00:06:03,938
- Really?
- Its frequency of use is quite high.

109
00:06:04,338 --> 00:06:05,339
It is used quite a lot.

110
00:06:05,339 --> 00:06:06,440
(Marketable, preferred ingredient)

111
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:08,874
Min Su is using yuzu.

112
00:06:10,744 --> 00:06:12,478
Is he making yuzu zest right now?

113
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:15,715
It looks like he's making zest
to bring out the scent.

114
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:18,752
Since he was the one who performed best
in the last mission,

115
00:06:18,752 --> 00:06:20,119
I have high expectations.

116
00:06:20,521 --> 00:06:23,423
He said he'd show us a dish
that doesn't exist in this world today.

117
00:06:23,423 --> 00:06:24,858
(Before the competition started)

118
00:06:25,492 --> 00:06:28,228
(A new dessert
that does not exist in this world)

119
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:31,264
(Min Su showed immense determination.)

120
00:06:31,699 --> 00:06:33,833
What is he making right now?

121
00:06:34,402 --> 00:06:36,269
The menu I've prepared today is...

122
00:06:36,530 --> 00:06:39,999
Geoje Yuzu Crepe Noodle Duo,
using yuzu from Geoje.

123
00:06:41,408 --> 00:06:45,145
(Geoje, a city embracing
the romance of the South Sea)

124
00:06:47,515 --> 00:06:48,949
(Golden Geoje yuzu of the South Sea)

125
00:06:48,949 --> 00:06:51,583
(Characterized by its refreshing
and fragrant aroma)

126
00:06:52,319 --> 00:06:55,923
Something I thought about a lot
while planning this dish was...

127
00:06:56,323 --> 00:06:57,858
that when I made the dessert,

128
00:06:57,858 --> 00:07:00,359
I wanted it to evoke
the feeling of that region.

129
00:07:00,528 --> 00:07:03,963
So, the motif I used was
Geoje Mongdol Beach.

130
00:07:04,630 --> 00:07:05,992
(Geoje Hakdong Mongdol Beach)

131
00:07:06,017 --> 00:07:09,203
(A beach in Geoje made of black pebbles
that look like black pearls)

132
00:07:09,203 --> 00:07:11,838
By turning the sunrise scene
of Mongdol Beach...

133
00:07:11,874 --> 00:07:14,474
into an image for the dessert,

134
00:07:14,909 --> 00:07:17,912
I tried to capture both fun and flavor.

135
00:07:17,912 --> 00:07:19,078
(Capturing both fun and flavor)

136
00:07:20,447 --> 00:07:22,949
(After separating all the pulp
and peel of the yuzu)

137
00:07:25,387 --> 00:07:27,754
(Cutting board and knife?)

138
00:07:29,523 --> 00:07:32,794
(Blanching the peels in water
after prepping them)

139
00:07:33,427 --> 00:07:35,204
Using them blanched like that means...

140
00:07:35,229 --> 00:07:37,029
he's planning to use the peel itself.

141
00:07:39,933 --> 00:07:41,468
He's going to make the peel edible.

142
00:07:41,468 --> 00:07:44,604
He's going to waste nothing.

143
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:46,507
In ice water?

144
00:07:46,507 --> 00:07:47,974
(Cooling the blanched yuzu peels
in ice water)

145
00:07:49,944 --> 00:07:52,612
It looks like he's going to make
yuzu confit.

146
00:07:53,347 --> 00:07:54,548
Yuzu confit.

147
00:07:54,548 --> 00:07:55,235
(Confit)

148
00:07:55,260 --> 00:07:56,743
(A French method where ingredients
are submerged...)

149
00:07:56,768 --> 00:07:57,851
(in syrup or oil and slow-simmered)

150
00:07:59,119 --> 00:08:02,088
Confit usually takes
more than five days to make,

151
00:08:02,088 --> 00:08:04,225
so it won't be easy to do it
in four hours.

152
00:08:04,225 --> 00:08:05,226
(Difficult within four hours)

153
00:08:05,226 --> 00:08:06,227
Will he succeed?

154
00:08:08,362 --> 00:08:10,897
Min Su starts blanching.

155
00:08:12,198 --> 00:08:13,200
(Cannoli Prince, Seong Min Su)

156
00:08:14,435 --> 00:08:17,069
(While making the confit)

157
00:08:18,138 --> 00:08:20,996
(Squeezing yuzu juice)

158
00:08:23,244 --> 00:08:25,245
Now he's squeezing the yuzu juice.

159
00:08:30,851 --> 00:08:33,687
(Yuzu cream sabayon made
with the extracted juice)

160
00:08:34,889 --> 00:08:35,988
(Sabayon)

161
00:08:36,013 --> 00:08:39,113
(A soft and light sauce made
by whisking egg yolks and sugar...)

162
00:08:39,137 --> 00:08:40,660
(over a double boiler)

163
00:08:45,132 --> 00:08:47,368
(Extracting juice once more)

164
00:08:47,969 --> 00:08:50,002
He's still squeezing juice.

165
00:08:57,178 --> 00:08:58,212
(Yuzu juice and zest...)

166
00:08:58,212 --> 00:09:01,380
(are added into the yuzu cream sabayon.)

167
00:09:03,918 --> 00:09:06,587
(Refreshing yuzu cream sabayon complete)

168
00:09:10,558 --> 00:09:13,427
(Adding batter water
to the Geoje yuzu powder)

169
00:09:15,229 --> 00:09:17,498
(Geoje mugwort powder)

170
00:09:18,265 --> 00:09:20,267
(Geoje paprika powder)

171
00:09:21,167 --> 00:09:22,802
The colors are so vibrant.

172
00:09:23,403 --> 00:09:26,439
Since I thought I could highlight
it with color,

173
00:09:26,439 --> 00:09:28,774
I tried making something to accompany it.

174
00:09:30,544 --> 00:09:32,378
Yuzu, mugwort...

175
00:09:32,913 --> 00:09:36,082
- Paprika.
- He added paprika.

176
00:09:38,017 --> 00:09:40,521
(What will the crepe look like?)

177
00:09:42,491 --> 00:09:45,259
(Clean job)

178
00:09:46,093 --> 00:09:47,161
A crepe?

179
00:09:47,561 --> 00:09:49,128
Crepes already exist.

180
00:09:51,665 --> 00:09:53,199
I will make a new dessert...

181
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:55,701
that does not exist in this world.

182
00:09:55,936 --> 00:09:57,903
He did say he'd make
something that doesn't exist.

183
00:09:58,238 --> 00:09:59,706
It'll be a big problem
if it already exists.

184
00:09:59,706 --> 00:10:02,275
He said he'd show us something
we've never seen before.

185
00:10:02,275 --> 00:10:03,628
It shouldn't come up
when you search for it.

186
00:10:03,653 --> 00:10:04,443
(Firm)

187
00:10:04,512 --> 00:10:07,013
Couldn't it be a different kind of crepe?

188
00:10:08,182 --> 00:10:10,851
I meant that I'm looking forward to it.

189
00:10:14,522 --> 00:10:16,288
I'm genuinely excited to see
what he comes up with.

190
00:10:21,295 --> 00:10:22,329
What is he doing?

191
00:10:24,498 --> 00:10:28,302
Slicing the crepe?

192
00:10:31,205 --> 00:10:33,874
- It looks like pasta.
- It's giving me pasta vibes.

193
00:10:34,642 --> 00:10:37,111
That is what I'm most worried about.

194
00:10:37,136 --> 00:10:38,737
(Wondering what the final product
will look like)

195
00:10:40,316 --> 00:10:44,189
Crepes are usually layered...

196
00:10:44,249 --> 00:10:45,751
and eaten as cakes,

197
00:10:47,127 --> 00:10:50,156
but since I wanted to create a dessert
that doesn't exist yet,

198
00:10:50,827 --> 00:10:52,492
I sliced the crepe.

199
00:10:52,646 --> 00:10:55,428
It's not common to eat a dessert
with a spoon like pasta.

200
00:10:56,057 --> 00:10:59,351
So I wanted to break that stereotype.

201
00:10:59,604 --> 00:11:05,671
And since I'm making a pastry
that represents the Geoje region,

202
00:11:06,257 --> 00:11:10,003
I wanted to express the waves
of the Geoje sea through the noodles.

203
00:11:10,622 --> 00:11:14,614
But normally, when we think of crepes,

204
00:11:14,728 --> 00:11:17,125
we think of spreading them out wide,
adding cream and fruit,

205
00:11:17,150 --> 00:11:18,218
and eating them that way.

206
00:11:18,718 --> 00:11:22,121
(A typical fruit crepe)

207
00:11:22,227 --> 00:11:25,934
- The amount of cream and fruit...
- You can pick and choose.

208
00:11:25,935 --> 00:11:28,967
If you approach it with the concept
of a dessert salad,

209
00:11:29,416 --> 00:11:31,309
I think it's a much better idea.

210
00:11:31,310 --> 00:11:32,721
(An idea that flips common sense)

211
00:11:32,721 --> 00:11:34,867
Where do ideas like that even come from?

212
00:11:39,978 --> 00:11:41,930
Mungyeong apples are so delicious.

213
00:11:42,210 --> 00:11:44,843
Kyung Joo is using Mungyeong apples.

214
00:11:45,884 --> 00:11:47,791
Another contestant is also using
the apple ingredient.

215
00:11:48,114 --> 00:11:51,284
(Gyeong Mu, who also chose apples)

216
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:52,827
It's the same ingredient.

217
00:11:52,851 --> 00:11:54,587
This will inevitably lead to a comparison.

218
00:11:55,113 --> 00:11:57,413
In the case of Gyeong Mu,

219
00:11:57,599 --> 00:12:01,936
I know he's good at everything,
whether it's confectionery or baking,

220
00:12:01,961 --> 00:12:03,129
so I was on guard.

221
00:12:03,291 --> 00:12:05,597
But wouldn't I be
just a little bit better?

222
00:12:05,598 --> 00:12:07,133
When the ingredients are the same,

223
00:12:07,471 --> 00:12:09,224
it'll be interesting to see...

224
00:12:09,248 --> 00:12:11,864
how they interpret
the story of the region.

225
00:12:14,273 --> 00:12:17,943
(Mungyeong, a historic gateway city)

226
00:12:19,447 --> 00:12:20,546
I need to look at the map.

227
00:12:22,347 --> 00:12:24,751
(After checking the map)

228
00:12:24,832 --> 00:12:27,636
I focused on the tourist spots
people visit the most,

229
00:12:27,660 --> 00:12:28,979
like Mungyeong Saejae,

230
00:12:29,338 --> 00:12:31,692
and traveled a bit
to the north, south, east, and west.

231
00:12:31,885 --> 00:12:35,028
The three local specialties are apples,

232
00:12:35,661 --> 00:12:37,363
(Mungyeong's representative specialty:
apples)

233
00:12:37,675 --> 00:12:38,727
Yakdol pork,

234
00:12:38,728 --> 00:12:40,166
(Mungyeong's representative specialty:
Yakdol pork)

235
00:12:40,271 --> 00:12:41,271
and schisandra.

236
00:12:41,272 --> 00:12:42,801
(Mungyeong's representative specialty:
schisandra)

237
00:12:42,834 --> 00:12:45,846
I wanted to try using all three of these.

238
00:12:46,013 --> 00:12:49,704
Pork in the east, apples in the west,

239
00:12:49,717 --> 00:12:51,911
and schisandra in the south.

240
00:12:52,052 --> 00:12:55,735
To bring that vision to life,
I've made apples the centerpiece,

241
00:12:55,759 --> 00:12:57,883
creating
a Moist Caramel Apple Baked Pastry,

242
00:12:58,297 --> 00:13:01,137
a Schisandra Nougat Crunchy Cookie
to highlight the schisandra,

243
00:13:01,643 --> 00:13:06,772
and finally, a Yakdol Pork Pastry Brunch
to showcase the pork.

244
00:13:07,227 --> 00:13:09,863
With the hope that it becomes
a city of bakeries,

245
00:13:09,895 --> 00:13:14,142
I had the idea of getting people to enjoy
pastries throughout Mungyeong.

246
00:13:14,522 --> 00:13:16,041
She says she's using all three.

247
00:13:16,065 --> 00:13:19,235
But she's making them
into three different types.

248
00:13:20,175 --> 00:13:22,487
Is Kyung Joo being
a bit too ambitious today?

249
00:13:22,488 --> 00:13:26,107
Excessive greed can lead to disaster.

250
00:13:26,180 --> 00:13:27,770
- There's quite a lot going on.
- Yes.

251
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:32,718
- What is that?
- What's that?

252
00:13:32,876 --> 00:13:33,719
Schisandra?

253
00:13:34,113 --> 00:13:35,921
- Schisandra.
- It's schisandra syrup.

254
00:13:37,590 --> 00:13:39,659
(After boiling schisandra syrup
and sugar together)

255
00:13:41,961 --> 00:13:45,064
(Adding apples and simmering them down)

256
00:13:47,871 --> 00:13:50,435
(Creating a baked pastry dough,
even adding pecans)

257
00:13:54,473 --> 00:13:56,742
(Maximizing sweetness with caramel sauce)

258
00:14:04,635 --> 00:14:05,985
I want to try that.

259
00:14:09,248 --> 00:14:11,891
(Followed by a sweet chocolate coating)

260
00:14:11,892 --> 00:14:12,990
That looks so delicious.

261
00:14:13,015 --> 00:14:14,618
Looks tasty.

262
00:14:15,340 --> 00:14:19,234
I think Kyung Joo's work has always
been visually spectacular.

263
00:14:19,814 --> 00:14:21,075
- Right.
- It's shaped like an apple.

264
00:14:21,813 --> 00:14:27,146
The way these two express
the apple is really...

265
00:14:27,453 --> 00:14:28,621
Since two people do apples,

266
00:14:28,645 --> 00:14:31,410
- we'll have to look very closely later.
- Exactly.

267
00:14:33,192 --> 00:14:36,982
The region I chose is
Jeongseon, Gangwon-do.

268
00:14:38,604 --> 00:14:43,644
When I thought of Jeongseon,
I was worried about the ingredients.

269
00:14:44,562 --> 00:14:46,725
Jeongseon is known for its apples.

270
00:14:46,776 --> 00:14:51,422
Apples are a great material to use
in confectionery and baking,

271
00:14:52,331 --> 00:14:53,566
This is incredibly sweet!

272
00:14:53,748 --> 00:14:55,781
What I loved when I ate
a Jeongseon apple...

273
00:14:56,208 --> 00:14:58,137
was that it was refreshing
but also very crunchy.

274
00:14:58,708 --> 00:15:03,814
Trying to capture that exact texture is
what I'm focusing on for this mission.

275
00:15:04,619 --> 00:15:08,280
But the ingredient could be
too predictable.

276
00:15:09,093 --> 00:15:11,817
(Apples, which are already
commonly used in pastry)

277
00:15:12,692 --> 00:15:17,991
I was worried about how to interpret this
in a way that feels like Jeongseon.

278
00:15:19,838 --> 00:15:20,789
For the components,

279
00:15:20,813 --> 00:15:22,761
I think apples and choux will go
really well together.

280
00:15:22,785 --> 00:15:23,863
It's refreshing.

281
00:15:24,110 --> 00:15:25,964
Choux is difficult, though.

282
00:15:26,957 --> 00:15:29,529
Is this place cursed?

283
00:15:30,903 --> 00:15:32,638
They keep trying to do choux.

284
00:15:32,678 --> 00:15:35,174
Every time they do choux,
they keep failing.

285
00:15:36,328 --> 00:15:39,200
Contestants who made choux
during the competition...

286
00:15:40,227 --> 00:15:41,614
kept getting poor results.

287
00:15:42,974 --> 00:15:45,784
(In Seok made biscuit choux
during the first round...)

288
00:15:46,622 --> 00:15:49,215
(but was eliminated
because his choux didn't rise.)

289
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:52,057
(And even in the Round 2 team mission,
the choux dough caused trouble.)

290
00:15:52,239 --> 00:15:54,026
But I felt that ambition again.

291
00:15:54,056 --> 00:15:54,760
"Right."

292
00:15:55,586 --> 00:15:58,446
"It'll be different if I do it."

293
00:15:58,699 --> 00:16:00,866
I really wanted to make choux.

294
00:16:04,719 --> 00:16:08,641
(Will Gyeong Mu's choux lead
to a different result?)

295
00:16:14,613 --> 00:16:18,217
(After piping the choux dough into molds)

296
00:16:22,608 --> 00:16:26,558
He froze the dough, unmolded it,
and he'll bake it now.

297
00:16:30,308 --> 00:16:32,667
Is he putting a cookie
on top of this one too?

298
00:16:32,691 --> 00:16:33,632
A cookie choux.

299
00:16:34,326 --> 00:16:38,103
- Since it's an apple, did he use red?
- It looks like it.

300
00:16:38,804 --> 00:16:39,804
(Cookie choux)

301
00:16:39,805 --> 00:16:40,746
I thought those were mushrooms.

302
00:16:40,770 --> 00:16:44,743
They spread out into a round shape
as they bake.

303
00:16:44,958 --> 00:16:47,785
The cookie acts as a wrapper.

304
00:16:47,786 --> 00:16:51,550
It helps the choux come out
in a consistent shape without bursting.

305
00:16:52,151 --> 00:16:53,786
They're going to look just like apples.

306
00:17:04,575 --> 00:17:07,506
- They really do wrap around as they cook.
- Yeah.

307
00:17:07,530 --> 00:17:08,627
- That's amazing.
- It is.

308
00:17:13,287 --> 00:17:16,442
Even though I came here having carefully
considered the making process,

309
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:19,278
you never know
how the choux will turn out.

310
00:17:19,393 --> 00:17:21,147
Until the choux went into the oven...

311
00:17:21,746 --> 00:17:24,450
and I could see them rising,

312
00:17:25,092 --> 00:17:27,720
I felt so uneasy,
and the process was sluggish.

313
00:17:28,683 --> 00:17:30,989
"If the choux fails,
I might as well pack my bags."

314
00:17:32,480 --> 00:17:34,933
Please, let the choux be a success.

315
00:17:39,431 --> 00:17:41,466
(Beep-beep-beep)

316
00:17:42,301 --> 00:17:44,236
(Sound of the oven timer)

317
00:17:45,712 --> 00:17:47,272
Ah, I'm saved.

318
00:17:50,738 --> 00:17:52,478
The choux has risen perfectly now.

319
00:17:52,503 --> 00:17:53,571
This is it.

320
00:17:53,764 --> 00:17:55,764
Didn't the choux turn out really well?

321
00:17:55,790 --> 00:17:57,790
The choux are coming out beautifully.

322
00:17:57,863 --> 00:18:00,874
So far, choux hasn't yielded
any good results.

323
00:18:00,898 --> 00:18:01,504
I know.

324
00:18:01,529 --> 00:18:03,066
It's been "one shot, one kill"
in a bad way.

325
00:18:03,066 --> 00:18:04,422
He definitely has the experience.

326
00:18:04,762 --> 00:18:05,762
He's on another level.

327
00:18:06,008 --> 00:18:07,326
"Everyone, look at this."

328
00:18:08,522 --> 00:18:10,992
I thought to myself,
"What's so hard about choux?"

329
00:18:11,045 --> 00:18:15,167
And as the other challengers
walked by, saying,

330
00:18:16,124 --> 00:18:18,025
"I knew you'd nail it," it felt great.

331
00:18:18,170 --> 00:18:20,339
(Feeling good)

332
00:18:21,843 --> 00:18:24,036
(The sound of sawing this time?)

333
00:18:24,037 --> 00:18:25,037
What is this?

334
00:18:28,216 --> 00:18:30,415
- He's peeling the choux like an apple.
- I know, right?

335
00:18:33,485 --> 00:18:35,135
(Starting to fill the choux
with caramel cream)

336
00:18:35,136 --> 00:18:36,388
With the caramel cream,

337
00:18:38,328 --> 00:18:39,892
I'm also adding apple compote.

338
00:18:42,281 --> 00:18:44,388
- He's filling the choux.
- That looks delicious.

339
00:18:44,412 --> 00:18:46,832
- I'm so excited.
- The choux turned out so well.

340
00:18:48,807 --> 00:18:50,335
He's topping it with apple chips.

341
00:18:51,370 --> 00:18:52,805
(And)

342
00:18:54,699 --> 00:18:57,610
One is a red "Ruby Choux,"

343
00:18:58,551 --> 00:19:01,186
and the other is a "Black Gold Choux"...

344
00:19:01,210 --> 00:19:03,199
to capture the vibe
of a coal or gold mine.

345
00:19:03,248 --> 00:19:05,217
I prepared these two choux products.

346
00:19:05,784 --> 00:19:09,836
The Black Gold Choux is filled
with vanilla cream and apple compote,

347
00:19:10,489 --> 00:19:12,024
and I also expressed elements
of a gold mine.

348
00:19:12,829 --> 00:19:14,826
I believe I've captured all of Jeongseon.

349
00:19:16,094 --> 00:19:18,129
(Meanwhile)

350
00:19:19,097 --> 00:19:21,766
(Kyung Joo starts grilling meat.)

351
00:19:21,793 --> 00:19:24,703
Oh my, what is that?
It's that Yakdol pork from earlier.

352
00:19:25,467 --> 00:19:26,673
She's actually using it?

353
00:19:26,697 --> 00:19:28,440
How is she planning to use Yakdol pork?

354
00:19:29,946 --> 00:19:32,988
The pork didn't have any gamey odor
when grilled.

355
00:19:33,013 --> 00:19:34,435
Since I was confident in that,

356
00:19:34,459 --> 00:19:37,849
I just grilled it
without any odor-removing steps.

357
00:19:39,861 --> 00:19:42,361
That looks so good.
I want to grill a piece and eat it.

358
00:19:42,361 --> 00:19:45,236
You'd have to wrap it in lettuce
with some ssamjang.

359
00:19:45,261 --> 00:19:47,500
Don't you think a lot of new pastries
will come out today?

360
00:19:47,525 --> 00:19:48,519
- It seems so.
- Yes.

361
00:19:48,687 --> 00:19:50,353
- She's even grilling pork.
- Right.

362
00:19:50,354 --> 00:19:54,523
Actually, pork and apple are
a very classic and delicious combination.

363
00:19:54,722 --> 00:19:56,735
It seems Kyung Joo did extensive research.

364
00:19:56,760 --> 00:19:58,387
Studying and learning...

365
00:20:01,402 --> 00:20:02,875
She's drawing something again.

366
00:20:04,015 --> 00:20:06,245
- Kyung Joo is really...
- Even the fine details?

367
00:20:06,246 --> 00:20:07,346
(Schisandra chocolates
cut out with a mold)

368
00:20:10,332 --> 00:20:12,718
- What is that?
- Macadamia nuts.

369
00:20:12,846 --> 00:20:16,033
Nougat is basically
like the Korean "yeot."

370
00:20:16,034 --> 00:20:18,257
- It's white and full of nuts.
- I love nougat.

371
00:20:18,536 --> 00:20:20,313
- She's doing this too?
- She's incredible.

372
00:20:20,337 --> 00:20:22,561
- She's doing so much today.
- She's the one...

373
00:20:22,562 --> 00:20:24,464
- who's working the hardest today.
- That's right.

374
00:20:27,184 --> 00:20:29,467
(Working while catching her breath)

375
00:20:30,970 --> 00:20:32,938
(What kind of task will it be this time?)

376
00:20:33,063 --> 00:20:34,939
- Pastry?
- She's even doing pastry?

377
00:20:35,302 --> 00:20:37,489
That requires a lot of manual labor.

378
00:20:37,514 --> 00:20:39,214
- Is it two-toned?
- She's even doing it two-toned.

379
00:20:42,708 --> 00:20:44,574
I could have just used plain white dough,

380
00:20:44,574 --> 00:20:47,674
but I also used black cocoa dough.

381
00:20:47,674 --> 00:20:49,241
It's for the look.

382
00:20:49,241 --> 00:20:52,741
I wanted to show my technical skills
more clearly.

383
00:20:52,741 --> 00:20:55,238
And I wanted the textures
to come together crisply,

384
00:20:55,239 --> 00:20:56,474
so that's how I made it.

385
00:20:56,941 --> 00:21:00,641
People asked,
"Can you really pull that off?"

386
00:21:00,641 --> 00:21:02,708
I'll get a thrill
out of proving them wrong.

387
00:21:04,708 --> 00:21:08,041
(The pastry dough is rolled
through the pie roller,)

388
00:21:09,841 --> 00:21:12,608
(then cut into squares.)

389
00:21:13,841 --> 00:21:16,408
(Topped with apples, lotus root,
and seasoned Yakdol pork)

390
00:21:17,574 --> 00:21:19,084
So that's how she reinterpreted it.

391
00:21:23,008 --> 00:21:23,941
It looks delicious.

392
00:21:24,541 --> 00:21:25,474
Look at that detail.

393
00:21:26,274 --> 00:21:27,841
Her technique is solid.

394
00:21:27,841 --> 00:21:29,574
- She's fast.
- She's good.

395
00:21:29,574 --> 00:21:33,008
As expected, I was a fool to doubt her.

396
00:21:33,974 --> 00:21:34,841
Indeed.

397
00:21:34,841 --> 00:21:38,208
She's a contestant
who has won a world competition.

398
00:21:38,208 --> 00:21:42,008
The sheer variety and volume required
in competitions are overwhelming.

399
00:21:42,008 --> 00:21:42,974
It's intense.

400
00:21:42,974 --> 00:21:44,308
- There's so much to do.
- True.

401
00:21:44,874 --> 00:21:46,308
And she's doing all that
without a single mistake.

402
00:21:46,308 --> 00:21:47,174
She's definitely a frontrunner.

403
00:21:48,108 --> 00:21:49,014
She's on another level.

404
00:21:51,741 --> 00:21:52,941
- Oh my.
- It's so pretty.

405
00:21:52,941 --> 00:21:54,374
She made it so beautifully.

406
00:21:55,441 --> 00:21:57,208
Her pastry is beautiful.

407
00:21:57,208 --> 00:21:58,108
This is amazing.

408
00:21:59,574 --> 00:22:01,141
- The level of detail is different.
- Exactly.

409
00:22:01,141 --> 00:22:03,308
But when you bake it in a mold like that,

410
00:22:03,308 --> 00:22:05,608
it puts pressure on the dough,

411
00:22:05,608 --> 00:22:08,708
so the baking and fermentation levels
are crucial.

412
00:22:08,708 --> 00:22:11,308
I'm curious to see the cross-section.

413
00:22:13,741 --> 00:22:16,574
(She starts the third menu,
Schisandra Nougat Cookie.)

414
00:22:27,341 --> 00:22:30,874
(Rolling the cookie
from the oven around a rod)

415
00:22:34,608 --> 00:22:35,908
How cute. What is that?

416
00:22:36,574 --> 00:22:37,941
- What is it?
- It's beautiful.

417
00:22:37,941 --> 00:22:39,941
It's another one of Kyung Joo's works,
right?

418
00:22:40,374 --> 00:22:41,908
The detail is insane.

419
00:22:42,274 --> 00:22:45,108
If you shape it while it's hot...

420
00:22:46,608 --> 00:22:48,674
it sets as it cools.

421
00:22:48,674 --> 00:22:51,708
If you make it thinner,

422
00:22:51,708 --> 00:22:56,041
it becomes a cigar-shaped wafer roll.

423
00:22:56,041 --> 00:22:57,208
With cream inside.

424
00:22:57,908 --> 00:22:59,341
You can make it like that,

425
00:22:59,541 --> 00:23:01,074
or even create patterns.

426
00:23:01,074 --> 00:23:02,374
It can be used in so many ways.

427
00:23:02,374 --> 00:23:04,556
All sorts of techniques are coming out.

428
00:23:06,474 --> 00:23:10,974
I don't think it's easy to keep up
with my technical skills.

429
00:23:12,708 --> 00:23:13,889
- What's that?
- What is she doing?

430
00:23:14,074 --> 00:23:15,941
- Schisandra.
- Schisandra syrup.

431
00:23:15,941 --> 00:23:17,641
(Adding schisandra syrup
as a highlight inside the dough)

432
00:23:20,974 --> 00:23:22,874
That cookie and the nougat will be
a perfect pair.

433
00:23:22,875 --> 00:23:24,017
(Topped with macadamias and nougat)

434
00:23:24,308 --> 00:23:25,608
It looks delicious.

435
00:23:35,108 --> 00:23:38,274
(Which region did Hwa Young choose?)

436
00:23:40,040 --> 00:23:43,773
I didn't know passion fruit was grown
in Korea now.

437
00:23:45,973 --> 00:23:47,540
(Crunch)

438
00:23:47,541 --> 00:23:49,157
My assigned region is Namwon,
Jeollanam-do,

439
00:23:49,158 --> 00:23:50,241
where passion fruit is produced.

440
00:23:50,241 --> 00:23:52,774
I'm going to make a dessert
using passion fruit.

441
00:23:53,808 --> 00:23:56,608
(Namwon, a traditional city
famous for its love story)

442
00:23:57,641 --> 00:23:59,241
The air is definitely great here.

443
00:24:00,674 --> 00:24:03,408
(Visiting a passion fruit farm in Namwon)

444
00:24:03,408 --> 00:24:04,808
Hello.

445
00:24:05,308 --> 00:24:06,941
- Is this "backhyanggwa?"
- Yes, it is.

446
00:24:06,941 --> 00:24:10,141
It's my first time seeing it in person.

447
00:24:10,141 --> 00:24:12,208
It's no overstatement to say...

448
00:24:12,208 --> 00:24:16,908
you get the taste and nutrition
of a hundred fruits in just one bite.

449
00:24:16,908 --> 00:24:21,741
People love the seeds
because of their crunchy texture.

450
00:24:21,741 --> 00:24:24,841
Since you say that, I'll keep the seeds,

451
00:24:25,674 --> 00:24:26,808
maintain the aroma,

452
00:24:28,508 --> 00:24:29,908
and emphasize the sweetness.

453
00:24:29,908 --> 00:24:32,408
My product will be...

454
00:24:32,408 --> 00:24:34,674
a passion fruit financier.

455
00:24:34,674 --> 00:24:36,808
He's making financiers!

456
00:24:36,808 --> 00:24:41,308
It must be tricky to capture
the passion fruit aroma with that pastry.

457
00:24:41,308 --> 00:24:43,508
I'm curious how he'll express it,

458
00:24:43,508 --> 00:24:45,774
since it's a fruit
with high moisture content.

459
00:24:45,774 --> 00:24:48,641
A financier is traditionally...

460
00:24:48,641 --> 00:24:53,141
a baked pastry meant to highlight
the nuts inside.

461
00:24:53,141 --> 00:24:55,808
But today, to highlight the passion fruit,

462
00:24:55,808 --> 00:24:57,974
I added five different flavors.

463
00:24:58,774 --> 00:25:02,474
Plain passion fruit as the base,

464
00:25:02,474 --> 00:25:04,474
then combinations with orange,

465
00:25:04,474 --> 00:25:05,841
mango,

466
00:25:06,174 --> 00:25:07,574
coconut,

467
00:25:07,574 --> 00:25:09,874
and Earl Grey.

468
00:25:09,874 --> 00:25:12,441
I made a combo with five varieties.

469
00:25:12,841 --> 00:25:15,274
I don't think I've seen it in Korea.
I saw it abroad.

470
00:25:15,274 --> 00:25:16,474
I ate it a lot abroad too,

471
00:25:16,474 --> 00:25:18,808
but I had no idea it was produced
in Korea.

472
00:25:23,408 --> 00:25:25,208
Usually, when making a financier,

473
00:25:25,208 --> 00:25:27,474
you just put the batter in the mold
and bake it immediately.

474
00:25:27,841 --> 00:25:30,941
You don't usually put anything
inside the batter.

475
00:25:32,574 --> 00:25:34,074
(But...)

476
00:25:36,641 --> 00:25:39,308
(he's putting passion fruit
inside the batter?)

477
00:25:42,141 --> 00:25:44,241
This time, to keep the seeds...

478
00:25:44,241 --> 00:25:45,741
I baked it with passion fruit seeds
inside.

479
00:25:46,508 --> 00:25:47,341
Oh.

480
00:25:48,374 --> 00:25:49,641
Will this be okay?

481
00:25:50,041 --> 00:25:51,574
Did he put the seeds in whole?

482
00:25:52,041 --> 00:25:54,508
He's putting the whole seeds in, right?

483
00:25:54,508 --> 00:25:55,408
Yes.

484
00:25:56,041 --> 00:25:59,974
There's pulp left inside the seeds.

485
00:25:59,974 --> 00:26:03,941
Sometimes the seeds are prepped
by washing, drying, and soaking first.

486
00:26:03,941 --> 00:26:07,941
That's one way to use
the seeds' crunchy texture.

487
00:26:07,941 --> 00:26:10,174
I'm curious how it'll turn out
in this case.

488
00:26:11,174 --> 00:26:14,008
(Hwa Young is still working elegantly.)

489
00:26:17,808 --> 00:26:21,774
(He checks the scale
after piping the batter.)

490
00:26:22,540 --> 00:26:25,073
I got held up at the scale
for quite a while.

491
00:26:25,074 --> 00:26:28,708
When you pipe the batter, it takes
a few seconds for the numbers to show up.

492
00:26:28,708 --> 00:26:31,141
That time really added up.

493
00:26:36,074 --> 00:26:38,074
Two hours have passed.

494
00:26:38,074 --> 00:26:39,941
The remaining time is two hours.

495
00:26:43,441 --> 00:26:44,274
He's just...

496
00:26:44,541 --> 00:26:45,774
He's so meticulous.

497
00:26:45,774 --> 00:26:48,608
Even while he's pressed for time,
he weighs everything on the scale.

498
00:26:48,608 --> 00:26:50,148
If it were me, I would've just winged it.

499
00:26:51,174 --> 00:26:53,108
I thought that was the right way to do it.

500
00:26:53,508 --> 00:26:57,274
That's the only way to ensure
the same flavor...

501
00:26:57,274 --> 00:26:59,308
and texture for every piece.

502
00:26:59,308 --> 00:27:01,274
If I were being careless,
I would've just used a spoon.

503
00:27:02,074 --> 00:27:03,508
I didn't want to do that.

504
00:27:04,508 --> 00:27:07,408
Everyone, there is one hour remaining.

505
00:27:08,141 --> 00:27:10,408
There's only about an hour left.

506
00:27:11,074 --> 00:27:14,141
Honestly, during my practice,

507
00:27:14,141 --> 00:27:17,041
I could finish the same task
in about two hours.

508
00:27:17,041 --> 00:27:19,708
I don't know why, but...

509
00:27:19,708 --> 00:27:21,574
time started slipping away.

510
00:27:21,574 --> 00:27:23,841
And when I finally did the math later,

511
00:27:23,841 --> 00:27:26,608
I realized I wouldn't be able
to bake everything in time.

512
00:27:30,241 --> 00:27:31,841
Gosh, he really needs to hurry.

513
00:27:31,841 --> 00:27:33,008
(Speed is more important than detail.)

514
00:27:33,974 --> 00:27:35,908
He looks very stressed.

515
00:27:36,208 --> 00:27:38,674
Since I'm rooting for him,
I'm getting worried.

516
00:27:44,141 --> 00:27:46,908
Everyone, 30 minutes left.

517
00:27:47,208 --> 00:27:50,574
You need to hurry now.

518
00:27:50,574 --> 00:27:51,474
Okay.

519
00:27:53,774 --> 00:27:56,708
(But he's only just begun
to make the orange financiers.)

520
00:27:58,608 --> 00:27:59,441
This won't do.

521
00:28:01,774 --> 00:28:05,974
(Switching tools
from chopsticks to a spoon)

522
00:28:07,241 --> 00:28:10,508
I feel like I lost my grace today.

523
00:28:10,508 --> 00:28:14,974
If you don't finish plating on time,
you're disqualified.

524
00:28:14,974 --> 00:28:17,674
I had to avoid that at the very least,

525
00:28:17,674 --> 00:28:20,574
so I couldn't be as elegant as usual.

526
00:28:21,908 --> 00:28:22,741
It's hot.

527
00:28:28,074 --> 00:28:30,708
(Hwa Young is breaking into a cold sweat.)

528
00:28:35,408 --> 00:28:36,091
Behind you.

529
00:28:36,092 --> 00:28:39,341
He was baking one tray at a time earlier,
but now he's baking two.

530
00:28:39,341 --> 00:28:42,541
- Because there's no time left.
- The time is really running out.

531
00:28:47,108 --> 00:28:49,641
There were only 20 minutes left,

532
00:28:50,041 --> 00:28:52,208
but financiers take 17 minutes to bake.

533
00:28:52,708 --> 00:28:55,274
So I had no choice but to bake
two trays at once.

534
00:28:55,274 --> 00:28:56,974
Otherwise,
I wouldn't have been able to submit them.

535
00:28:56,974 --> 00:29:00,408
That was the part I hated the most.

536
00:29:01,041 --> 00:29:03,141
(Time continues to tick away.)

537
00:29:06,374 --> 00:29:10,108
(Other contestants are already finishing
their packaging.)

538
00:29:15,741 --> 00:29:18,974
(Hwa Young sets up the boxes first.)

539
00:29:20,408 --> 00:29:22,274
(Oven beeping)

540
00:29:23,141 --> 00:29:25,941
(He runs to check the oven.)

541
00:29:28,308 --> 00:29:31,608
(Less than 3 minutes left now.)

542
00:29:36,341 --> 00:29:37,541
He's the busiest right now.

543
00:29:41,674 --> 00:29:43,474
If he starts packaging now...

544
00:29:43,474 --> 00:29:44,908
(Will he be able to finish packaging?)

545
00:29:48,374 --> 00:29:50,674
He's going for a buzzer-beater.

546
00:29:52,841 --> 00:29:55,274
He starts packaging the financiers.

547
00:29:55,274 --> 00:29:56,608
He seems really overwhelmed today.

548
00:29:59,441 --> 00:30:01,908
What I was most dissatisfied with was...

549
00:30:01,908 --> 00:30:04,341
that I had to skip the cooling process.

550
00:30:04,341 --> 00:30:07,041
I just went straight to packaging.

551
00:30:07,341 --> 00:30:08,974
Alright, one minute left.

552
00:30:12,341 --> 00:30:13,274
Hang in there.

553
00:30:14,508 --> 00:30:15,408
You can do it.

554
00:30:15,808 --> 00:30:16,674
Let's go.

555
00:30:19,474 --> 00:30:20,508
Hurry!

556
00:30:28,008 --> 00:30:31,408
(A battle against the clock)

557
00:30:34,441 --> 00:30:35,308
I'm done.

558
00:30:36,010 --> 00:30:38,910
The mission has ended.

559
00:30:42,216 --> 00:30:44,282
They say you're "sweating bullets"
in times like this.

560
00:30:44,283 --> 00:30:45,583
I truly felt it.

561
00:30:45,753 --> 00:30:49,290
"Is there a fruit called 'Baekhyanggwa?'
Does it taste good?"

562
00:30:49,290 --> 00:30:51,523
I made this to make people
curious like that and try.

563
00:30:52,360 --> 00:30:54,428
- Hey, you need some water, right?
- Yes, I do.

564
00:30:54,428 --> 00:30:56,664
I knew it. I already got it for you.

565
00:30:59,800 --> 00:31:01,167
Do the water and ice come out together?

566
00:31:01,168 --> 00:31:02,800
Fascinating.

567
00:31:03,637 --> 00:31:05,339
The ice comes out like a soda dispenser.

568
00:31:05,673 --> 00:31:07,073
It's crushed ice.

569
00:31:07,073 --> 00:31:09,276
- You really worked hard.
- It was tough.

570
00:31:12,179 --> 00:31:13,447
So refreshing.

571
00:31:13,447 --> 00:31:15,914
- The crunch of the ice is so good.
- So chilling.

572
00:31:16,150 --> 00:31:18,883
(Even the tense nerves are cooled down.)

573
00:31:19,319 --> 00:31:20,955
This is really something else.

574
00:31:20,955 --> 00:31:22,687
- It's even got a slim design.
- Totally.

575
00:31:23,357 --> 00:31:25,125
- Today was brutal.
- It really was.

576
00:31:25,358 --> 00:31:27,660
This round is definitely not easy.

577
00:31:27,661 --> 00:31:28,896
(They are cooling off with cold water.)

578
00:31:35,135 --> 00:31:36,134
And now,

579
00:31:36,838 --> 00:31:41,575
the judging for the "Local Heritage"
Semifinal will begin.

580
00:31:44,445 --> 00:31:47,014
Since this is the semifinal round,

581
00:31:47,014 --> 00:31:50,915
the judging will be conducted
in a different way.

582
00:31:51,719 --> 00:31:54,755
As soon as each contestant is finished,

583
00:31:54,755 --> 00:31:56,590
(After individual judging,)

584
00:31:56,590 --> 00:32:00,160
the masters' total scores will be revealed
on the spot.

585
00:32:01,295 --> 00:32:03,695
The rankings will update in real-time.

586
00:32:05,333 --> 00:32:06,700
(Semifinal rankings are
decided in real-time.)

587
00:32:06,700 --> 00:32:09,364
The top seven will advance to the finals.

588
00:32:10,305 --> 00:32:12,137
If you fall outside of that group,

589
00:32:12,940 --> 00:32:14,806
you'll be eliminated immediately.

590
00:32:16,910 --> 00:32:19,115
Depending on how others score,

591
00:32:19,116 --> 00:32:20,712
even if you're safe now,

592
00:32:21,349 --> 00:32:25,316
your fate could shift
to elimination later.

593
00:32:26,921 --> 00:32:28,083
First up,

594
00:32:28,448 --> 00:32:31,391
Fine-Dining Patissier, Yoon Hwa Young.

595
00:32:31,391 --> 00:32:32,793
(First evaluation: Yoon Hwa Young)

596
00:32:35,328 --> 00:32:37,097
Knowing how talented he is,

597
00:32:37,097 --> 00:32:39,934
I was really looking forward to his work.

598
00:32:40,367 --> 00:32:43,304
Hwa Young, please explain.

599
00:32:43,537 --> 00:32:47,107
I used passion fruit from Namwon...

600
00:32:47,675 --> 00:32:48,943
to make financiers.

601
00:32:49,543 --> 00:32:51,744
(Passionable:
Five Varieties of Passion Fruit Financier)

602
00:32:51,744 --> 00:32:53,114
Namwon is a popular spot,

603
00:32:53,115 --> 00:32:55,849
thanks to the famous hiking trails
of Jirisan Mountain.

604
00:32:56,258 --> 00:32:57,827
I wanted to create something...

605
00:32:57,852 --> 00:32:59,654
that could be stored
at room temperature...

606
00:32:59,654 --> 00:33:01,168
or kept in the freezer...

607
00:33:01,235 --> 00:33:04,743
so it can be enjoyed immediately
right after thawing.

608
00:33:06,493 --> 00:33:10,361
Passion fruit seeds are
usually quite tough and hard.

609
00:33:10,464 --> 00:33:12,733
But the Korean variety is a bit softer,

610
00:33:12,733 --> 00:33:15,199
with just enough crunch to be pleasant.

611
00:33:15,469 --> 00:33:18,206
I wanted to emphasize that unique trait.

612
00:33:18,206 --> 00:33:19,537
So I put them inside...

613
00:33:19,840 --> 00:33:22,576
with coconut, mango, orange,

614
00:33:22,576 --> 00:33:24,509
Earl Grey, and almond.

615
00:33:25,112 --> 00:33:30,114
You can enjoy five different flavors
based on Korean passion fruit.

616
00:33:31,452 --> 00:33:34,188
Then, we shall begin the tasting.

617
00:33:38,292 --> 00:33:39,523
Here.

618
00:33:39,524 --> 00:33:40,859
Thank you.

619
00:33:44,365 --> 00:33:45,566
"Passionable."

620
00:33:55,676 --> 00:33:58,245
(Crunch)

621
00:33:59,647 --> 00:34:03,347
(Was adding the seeds a wise move?)

622
00:34:16,163 --> 00:34:20,067
You used ingredients that pair
classically well with passion fruit.

623
00:34:20,401 --> 00:34:22,570
So I enjoyed it as well. However...

624
00:34:22,869 --> 00:34:24,837
had you had more time,

625
00:34:25,072 --> 00:34:27,241
I think you could've come up with a way...

626
00:34:27,241 --> 00:34:29,210
to make the seeds even more palatable.

627
00:34:29,210 --> 00:34:32,514
Right now, the texture of the seeds is...

628
00:34:32,514 --> 00:34:34,748
a little irritating.

629
00:34:34,748 --> 00:34:37,251
But the overall balance
of flavors was excellent.

630
00:34:37,251 --> 00:34:38,252
I enjoyed it.

631
00:34:39,954 --> 00:34:44,288
Did you use almond powder
or hazelnut powder in these?

632
00:34:44,592 --> 00:34:47,528
Financiers are traditionally pastries
where the nutty flavor takes center stage.

633
00:34:47,528 --> 00:34:50,397
But I felt the passion fruit was
getting lost because of that.

634
00:34:50,397 --> 00:34:52,733
So I swapped the brown butter
for clarified butter.

635
00:34:52,733 --> 00:34:56,300
I used the minimum amount of almond powder
and didn't use any hazelnut powder.

636
00:34:56,604 --> 00:34:59,106
Because you cut back on the almond powder,

637
00:34:59,640 --> 00:35:01,672
the texture became a bit tough.

638
00:35:02,008 --> 00:35:03,578
When you removed the hazelnut and butter,

639
00:35:03,578 --> 00:35:07,211
it would've been nice if you'd maintained
the moisture with something else.

640
00:35:07,481 --> 00:35:09,250
If you'd made a passion fruit syrup...

641
00:35:09,250 --> 00:35:11,884
and brushed it on after baking,

642
00:35:11,884 --> 00:35:15,154
that moisture would've held up
much longer.

643
00:35:15,154 --> 00:35:16,954
It's a bit of a shame.

644
00:35:19,761 --> 00:35:24,128
Masters, please record your scores.

645
00:35:29,471 --> 00:35:33,274
(Out of 600, how many points will he get?)

646
00:35:36,009 --> 00:35:38,045
Please reveal...

647
00:35:39,447 --> 00:35:41,779
the score of Hwa Young,

648
00:35:43,058 --> 00:35:44,318
our first semifinalist.

649
00:35:44,318 --> 00:35:46,453
(The score is...)

650
00:35:51,458 --> 00:35:54,394
(Hwa Young's total score: 424)

651
00:35:56,997 --> 00:35:58,065
Right.

652
00:35:58,699 --> 00:36:02,236
Fine-Dining Patissier,
Yoon Hwa Young earned...

653
00:36:02,236 --> 00:36:05,768
a total of 424 points.

654
00:36:06,941 --> 00:36:08,342
(Top 7 Ranking Announcement)

655
00:36:08,342 --> 00:36:11,042
He's in first place
as he's the first challenger.

656
00:36:19,019 --> 00:36:21,152
It's a bit disappointing, and I'm sorry.

657
00:36:21,755 --> 00:36:24,692
I wasn't able to execute it
exactly as I'd hoped.

658
00:36:27,528 --> 00:36:28,426
Next up,

659
00:36:28,796 --> 00:36:31,295
iba Cup No.2, Jang Kyung Joo.

660
00:36:31,465 --> 00:36:32,896
Please step forward to the judging table.

661
00:36:32,897 --> 00:36:33,965
(Second Evaluation: Jang Kyung Joo)

662
00:36:42,042 --> 00:36:44,044
Her work is so impressive.

663
00:36:44,845 --> 00:36:46,847
It'll be a masterpiece
if it tastes as good as it looks.

664
00:36:48,516 --> 00:36:50,317
(Everyone had high expectations
for Kyung Joo.)

665
00:36:50,751 --> 00:36:52,486
(Kyung Joo's region: Mungyeong)

666
00:36:52,486 --> 00:36:54,385
Please explain your local pastry.

667
00:36:55,456 --> 00:36:58,222
The region I have chosen is Mungyeong.

668
00:36:58,726 --> 00:37:00,961
Mungyeong's famous specialties are...

669
00:37:00,961 --> 00:37:04,991
apples, Yakdol pork, and schisandra.

670
00:37:04,999 --> 00:37:08,369
These are the three things
the area is known for.

671
00:37:08,602 --> 00:37:11,202
So I incorporated all of them.

672
00:37:11,572 --> 00:37:15,773
I created three products
based on each ingredient.

673
00:37:16,744 --> 00:37:17,811
Apples in the west,

674
00:37:17,811 --> 00:37:18,879
(Moist Caramel Apple Baked Pastry)

675
00:37:18,879 --> 00:37:20,581
The Yakdol pork in the east,

676
00:37:20,581 --> 00:37:21,549
(Yakdol Pork Pastry Brunch)

677
00:37:21,882 --> 00:37:23,284
and schisandra in the south.

678
00:37:23,284 --> 00:37:24,285
(Schisandra Nougat Crunchy Cookie)

679
00:37:24,285 --> 00:37:29,921
I made these hoping you could experience
Mungyeong all day long.

680
00:37:32,226 --> 00:37:35,593
(Tasting the apple baked good first)

681
00:37:47,314 --> 00:37:51,384
(Next, they taste the Yakdol pork pastry.)

682
00:38:03,224 --> 00:38:06,861
(The masters taste each item.)

683
00:38:11,532 --> 00:38:14,132
Did you get a chance to taste
all three of these today?

684
00:38:14,734 --> 00:38:16,404
I tasted them during testing,

685
00:38:16,404 --> 00:38:18,369
- But not today?
- No.

686
00:38:19,005 --> 00:38:21,609
They work well when eaten separately.

687
00:38:21,609 --> 00:38:24,942
The acidity of the schisandra
in the nougat is really good.

688
00:38:25,445 --> 00:38:27,281
As for the apple baked good,

689
00:38:27,748 --> 00:38:31,482
the presentation and texture were
excellent.

690
00:38:31,718 --> 00:38:34,987
And the Yakdol pork pastry.
This one was good too.

691
00:38:34,987 --> 00:38:36,557
It goes well with the apple.

692
00:38:36,557 --> 00:38:37,655
However,

693
00:38:37,656 --> 00:38:42,429
you suggested we start
with the Moist Caramel Apple Baked Pastry,

694
00:38:42,429 --> 00:38:44,695
but that actually had
the boldest flavor profile.

695
00:38:45,967 --> 00:38:48,602
So the delicate flavor of the pork...

696
00:38:48,903 --> 00:38:50,634
was mostly overshadowed.

697
00:38:52,773 --> 00:38:57,174
If you look at each component on its own,

698
00:38:57,378 --> 00:39:00,682
there's an immense amount
of technique involved.

699
00:39:00,682 --> 00:39:03,478
You made the two-tone pastry dough,

700
00:39:03,478 --> 00:39:05,052
langue de chat,

701
00:39:05,052 --> 00:39:07,721
tuile, chocolate,

702
00:39:07,721 --> 00:39:10,424
apple confit, baked goods,

703
00:39:10,424 --> 00:39:11,722
and even the nougat.

704
00:39:12,725 --> 00:39:15,895
Pulling all of this off
within the time limit is...

705
00:39:15,895 --> 00:39:20,297
a testament
to your flawless technical skill.

706
00:39:21,735 --> 00:39:24,235
But for today's competition...

707
00:39:24,972 --> 00:39:26,006
Well,

708
00:39:27,439 --> 00:39:31,101
it feels like the elements got muddled
because you tried to do too much.

709
00:39:31,945 --> 00:39:35,150
You might be surprised
when you taste this for yourself later.

710
00:39:35,150 --> 00:39:38,916
Speaking as someone who has done
a lot of food and beverage consulting,

711
00:39:39,119 --> 00:39:42,688
I've seen places that excel
with an a la carte menu...

712
00:39:42,689 --> 00:39:45,556
but struggle when they try
to design a course.

713
00:39:45,826 --> 00:39:50,694
You have to manage the flavors
by balancing the intensity,

714
00:39:50,880 --> 00:39:52,466
but here, every item feels
like a main dish.

715
00:39:52,466 --> 00:39:54,231
(The problem when everything stands out)

716
00:39:55,336 --> 00:39:58,772
Masters, please record your scores.

717
00:39:58,772 --> 00:40:01,238
(Entering the scores for Kyung Joo)

718
00:40:06,308 --> 00:40:08,648
(What score will she get?)

719
00:40:09,216 --> 00:40:12,217
It's time to reveal the scores.

720
00:40:13,153 --> 00:40:14,321
Please reveal...

721
00:40:15,089 --> 00:40:17,591
the score for iba Cup No.2,
Jang Kyung Joo.

722
00:40:18,492 --> 00:40:20,528
(Kyung Joo's score: 413)

723
00:40:20,528 --> 00:40:23,397
Kyung Joo, iba Cup No.2,

724
00:40:23,397 --> 00:40:26,800
you've got 413.

725
00:40:26,800 --> 00:40:28,434
(Kyung Joo's total score: 413)

726
00:40:29,470 --> 00:40:31,572
You are currently in second place.

727
00:40:31,572 --> 00:40:32,908
(Current Standings:
1st Hwa Young, 2nd Kyung Joo)

728
00:40:33,073 --> 00:40:35,916
Hwa Young, you've maintained
your hold on first place spot.

729
00:40:35,941 --> 00:40:37,441
(Succeeds in keeping his place)

730
00:40:41,287 --> 00:40:44,548
Maybe it produced the opposite effect
since I laid it all out there.

731
00:40:45,187 --> 00:40:46,851
Maybe I should've played it safe.

732
00:40:49,826 --> 00:40:52,356
The evaluations this time are no joke.

733
00:40:52,672 --> 00:40:54,959
They don't give as many points
this time around.

734
00:40:56,938 --> 00:41:00,297
I thought they'd get a better score.

735
00:41:01,200 --> 00:41:02,200
For both of them, actually.

736
00:41:02,587 --> 00:41:05,869
(The contestants are nervous seeing
the strict evaluations.)

737
00:41:06,752 --> 00:41:10,586
Next is the third contestant,
Dessert Macho, Lee Gyeong Mu.

738
00:41:17,518 --> 00:41:23,424
This time, I used the Jeongseon apple
as my theme.

739
00:41:23,910 --> 00:41:27,191
The foundation of this dish is the apple.

740
00:41:28,363 --> 00:41:31,695
I wanted to incorporate everything I could
about Jeongseon.

741
00:41:32,562 --> 00:41:35,432
First, here are the Ruby Choux
that I prepared.

742
00:41:35,574 --> 00:41:37,835
I wanted to express the appearance
of an apple with this one.

743
00:41:38,495 --> 00:41:43,474
Second, Jeongseon is famous
for gold mines,

744
00:41:44,121 --> 00:41:46,513
and I wanted to represent
some of Jeongseon's history.

745
00:41:47,639 --> 00:41:51,081
When we think of Jeongseon,
"Arirang" comes to mind.

746
00:41:51,280 --> 00:41:54,346
The birthplace of "Arirang" is
a river called Auraji...

747
00:41:54,612 --> 00:41:56,854
where several streams meet.

748
00:41:57,278 --> 00:42:02,028
I used their regional specialty,
gondre powder, and made three cookies.

749
00:42:02,308 --> 00:42:06,115
I wanted to show Jeongseon
in the packaging as well.

750
00:42:07,387 --> 00:42:08,432
It's beautiful.

751
00:42:10,013 --> 00:42:11,835
- It's pretty.
- It really is.

752
00:42:26,877 --> 00:42:29,720
(He took a confident challenge
with the Ruby Choux.)

753
00:42:34,396 --> 00:42:37,694
(Will he be acknowledged for its flavor?)

754
00:42:39,689 --> 00:42:43,334
Was there a reason you chose
choux as your main pastry?

755
00:42:43,967 --> 00:42:47,037
Actually, that was
an intentional decision.

756
00:42:48,907 --> 00:42:51,394
There hasn't been anyone on the show...

757
00:42:52,446 --> 00:42:55,146
who was able to get
a good score with choux.

758
00:42:56,239 --> 00:42:58,515
So I thought I'd give it a shot.

759
00:42:59,871 --> 00:43:03,184
What you were trying to achieve...

760
00:43:06,364 --> 00:43:07,546
was a success, I believe.

761
00:43:07,571 --> 00:43:09,770
In my opinion,

762
00:43:09,794 --> 00:43:12,603
this is the best choux
I've had on this show.

763
00:43:13,256 --> 00:43:14,256
It was delicious.

764
00:43:15,056 --> 00:43:17,656
I think Jeongseon may have
just been blessed.

765
00:43:18,412 --> 00:43:22,006
If they put this out as a product,

766
00:43:22,358 --> 00:43:25,242
I think it'll be a famous one
for the region.

767
00:43:25,878 --> 00:43:30,144
The flavor, style, brand storytelling,
and regional identity...

768
00:43:30,350 --> 00:43:32,650
all shone through.
It was a marvelous dish.

769
00:43:36,002 --> 00:43:39,389
The apples' boiled texture was great.

770
00:43:40,449 --> 00:43:43,694
But you diced the apples,

771
00:43:44,161 --> 00:43:47,865
and as you can see on the box,

772
00:43:48,467 --> 00:43:50,134
a lot of the apples fell off.

773
00:43:50,661 --> 00:43:52,587
If this is released as a product,

774
00:43:53,767 --> 00:43:58,075
I think it'll be difficult to transport.

775
00:44:02,389 --> 00:44:05,149
Today, we had
overlapping main ingredients.

776
00:44:05,195 --> 00:44:07,192
Kyung Joo also had apples,

777
00:44:07,216 --> 00:44:11,154
so it was a battle of Mungyeong apples
and Jeongseon apples.

778
00:44:11,648 --> 00:44:13,728
If I was able to properly present
the main ingredient,

779
00:44:13,752 --> 00:44:16,827
I believe I'll get a good score.

780
00:44:18,493 --> 00:44:21,125
Here are the results for Gyeong Mu.

781
00:44:34,210 --> 00:44:37,781
You received a final score of 519 points.

782
00:44:38,115 --> 00:44:41,318
(Dessert Macho, Lee Gyeong Mu, 519 points)

783
00:44:42,019 --> 00:44:43,877
(1st Lee Gyeong Mu, 2nd Yoon Hwa Young,
3rd Jang Kyung Joo)

784
00:44:43,902 --> 00:44:45,956
You're in first place.

785
00:44:47,852 --> 00:44:49,681
Hwa Young is in second,

786
00:44:50,681 --> 00:44:54,031
and Kyung Joo is in third.

787
00:44:54,585 --> 00:44:56,299
Please head over to the Pass Zone.

788
00:44:56,906 --> 00:44:58,502
- Congratulations.
- Well done.

789
00:44:59,625 --> 00:45:02,506
I knew it!

790
00:45:02,789 --> 00:45:05,343
(Gyeong Mu heads to the first-place spot.)

791
00:45:08,561 --> 00:45:11,940
I've never placed first
since being on this show.

792
00:45:11,964 --> 00:45:12,809
I was excited.

793
00:45:17,787 --> 00:45:20,958
Bukhansan Summit Bakery, Kim Jin Seo,

794
00:45:22,479 --> 00:45:27,331
please explain your K-Local Pastry
from Imsil, North Jeolla-do.

795
00:45:29,791 --> 00:45:30,791
Hello, everyone.

796
00:45:31,551 --> 00:45:33,904
I'm really nervous!

797
00:45:36,843 --> 00:45:41,178
You seemed to have gained
some weight since Round One.

798
00:45:41,908 --> 00:45:45,749
Since I have to keep tasting
as I prepare for each competition,

799
00:45:45,909 --> 00:45:49,287
instead of proofing the bread,
I guess I might've proofed myself.

800
00:45:51,128 --> 00:45:52,128
That was cute.

801
00:45:52,528 --> 00:45:55,523
The region I chose
for this mission is Imsil,

802
00:45:55,547 --> 00:45:57,161
and my ingredient is cheese.

803
00:45:58,796 --> 00:46:02,500
(Packing the pastry with Gouda cheese)

804
00:46:05,335 --> 00:46:06,497
(Wrapping the outside with cheese)

805
00:46:06,498 --> 00:46:09,406
Wrapping the outside in cheese,

806
00:46:09,910 --> 00:46:12,776
it shows the distinct identity of Imsil.

807
00:46:13,943 --> 00:46:17,475
I wanted you all to feel...

808
00:46:17,875 --> 00:46:21,228
the familiar flavor of mozzarella cheese.

809
00:46:21,655 --> 00:46:24,558
I thought it would be good
to create a dish...

810
00:46:24,582 --> 00:46:26,791
that you could share
as you tour around Imsil.

811
00:46:27,171 --> 00:46:29,593
What matched that the best was
a small lunchbox.

812
00:46:30,903 --> 00:46:32,447
As you are tasting the dish,

813
00:46:32,546 --> 00:46:36,823
first generously drizzle the honey
from the bottle on top.

814
00:46:37,514 --> 00:46:41,105
And for those who want to enjoy the aroma,
you can try it with basil.

815
00:46:41,561 --> 00:46:44,141
And for those who don't,

816
00:46:44,481 --> 00:46:47,711
you can eat it with the tomato
dipped in honey.

817
00:46:51,080 --> 00:46:52,080
Wow!

818
00:46:54,746 --> 00:46:55,746
Drizzle it on?

819
00:46:56,229 --> 00:46:58,198
- Yes, you must drizzle a lot.
- Sure!

820
00:46:58,223 --> 00:46:59,456
(Understood)

821
00:47:01,191 --> 00:47:02,893
(Generously drizzling)

822
00:47:04,761 --> 00:47:08,265
(A new, unique form
of Imsil Burrata Bread)

823
00:47:15,053 --> 00:47:18,776
(Will it be able to charter a new path
for cheese pastries?)

824
00:47:27,297 --> 00:47:29,019
Imsil cheese is delicious, right?

825
00:47:29,736 --> 00:47:32,188
It's the symbol of Korean cheese.

826
00:47:32,350 --> 00:47:35,192
I've seen mozzarella be used in a salad...

827
00:47:35,569 --> 00:47:38,429
or as a filling for a pastry.

828
00:47:39,075 --> 00:47:43,234
But this is the first time I'm seeing
it wrapped around a pastry.

829
00:47:43,274 --> 00:47:44,534
This idea is great.

830
00:47:47,040 --> 00:47:50,553
Eating it without the honey is better
for the balance of the dish.

831
00:47:50,627 --> 00:47:55,905
Just adding the honey makes
it extremely sweet,

832
00:47:55,906 --> 00:47:57,556
which masks the other flavors.

833
00:47:57,580 --> 00:47:59,650
If you wanted to add honey,

834
00:47:59,732 --> 00:48:01,573
playing with the tartness...

835
00:48:01,598 --> 00:48:06,223
or adding nuts would've
balanced it out better.

836
00:48:06,774 --> 00:48:08,091
That part was a bit disappointing.

837
00:48:09,607 --> 00:48:12,629
Personally, I thought
the honey made it delicious.

838
00:48:13,514 --> 00:48:15,794
That's my personal opinion,
since I like sweet things.

839
00:48:16,260 --> 00:48:17,743
If there wasn't any honey,

840
00:48:18,383 --> 00:48:20,971
I think the dish would've screamed
"Imsil cheese" too strongly.

841
00:48:21,017 --> 00:48:23,874
It would be hard to recognize
it as a pastry...

842
00:48:24,029 --> 00:48:25,676
and would feel more
like just merely cheese.

843
00:48:26,149 --> 00:48:29,435
The honey brought more harmony
to the dish and the chewy texture.

844
00:48:29,436 --> 00:48:31,145
And it made
the cheese flavor more pronounced.

845
00:48:31,169 --> 00:48:34,054
The combination with the cheese was
very nice.

846
00:48:37,597 --> 00:48:40,924
I enjoyed it more than I thought.

847
00:48:40,925 --> 00:48:43,263
The Gouda cheese filling had...

848
00:48:43,264 --> 00:48:45,629
a nutty flavor, which I liked.

849
00:48:46,136 --> 00:48:49,800
But I don't think the honey was
a good match.

850
00:48:51,042 --> 00:48:54,254
You provided a fork for us
to eat this with,

851
00:48:54,255 --> 00:48:56,101
but it was difficult to eat with it.

852
00:48:56,754 --> 00:49:00,110
I think you should've considered
that with the packaging as well.

853
00:49:02,657 --> 00:49:04,657
The current first-place spot...

854
00:49:05,442 --> 00:49:09,115
is held by Dessert Macho, Lee Gyeong Mu.

855
00:49:09,549 --> 00:49:12,589
Will Jin Seo...

856
00:49:13,328 --> 00:49:16,860
be able to enter the finals?
And with how many points?

857
00:49:18,874 --> 00:49:21,364
Let's check the results.

858
00:49:24,901 --> 00:49:27,971
(Bukhansan Summit Bakery,
Kim Jin Seo, 479 points)

859
00:49:27,972 --> 00:49:32,729
Jin Seo, you received
a total score of 479 points.

860
00:49:34,363 --> 00:49:36,202
(Top 7 Ranking: 2nd Kim Jin Seo)

861
00:49:36,203 --> 00:49:38,082
You are in second place.

862
00:49:40,368 --> 00:49:45,355
There haven't been any changes
for the current first place, Gyeong Mu.

863
00:49:46,506 --> 00:49:49,059
Hwa Young is in third,

864
00:49:49,913 --> 00:49:52,596
and Kyung Joo is in fourth.

865
00:49:53,645 --> 00:49:55,265
They each moved down a place.

866
00:49:55,955 --> 00:49:56,855
(Moving into the top rankings)

867
00:49:56,880 --> 00:49:58,168
- Congratulations.
- Well done.

868
00:50:03,807 --> 00:50:04,580
Next is...

869
00:50:05,206 --> 00:50:08,812
The News Anchor Who Bakes, Lee Hye Sung.

870
00:50:21,518 --> 00:50:24,027
(The contestant whose oven had issues)

871
00:50:26,984 --> 00:50:29,499
(The oven temperature rose
faster than expected.)

872
00:50:32,989 --> 00:50:36,606
(She did her best, even switching ovens
in the middle.)

873
00:50:44,708 --> 00:50:47,541
The original recipe requires
12 minutes of baking,

874
00:50:47,808 --> 00:50:49,741
but I think I baked it
for almost 20 minutes.

875
00:50:49,741 --> 00:50:54,108
So the sheet cake will inevitably be dry.

876
00:50:54,808 --> 00:50:57,308
Get in there.

877
00:50:57,308 --> 00:50:59,508
(A heart that desperately pleads)

878
00:51:01,108 --> 00:51:03,741
I placed the sheet cake
and added the filling.

879
00:51:03,741 --> 00:51:07,674
I've never felt this pressed for time.

880
00:51:10,208 --> 00:51:11,241
(Raspberry compote)

881
00:51:11,241 --> 00:51:13,574
(Kadayıf noodles and pistachio salad)

882
00:51:15,741 --> 00:51:17,708
(Narrowly completed)

883
00:51:19,008 --> 00:51:22,541
I want to make it to the finals
no matter what.

884
00:51:27,574 --> 00:51:31,608
(How will Hye Sung's dish be evaluated?)

885
00:51:33,508 --> 00:51:36,074
The name of the dish I prepared is...

886
00:51:36,501 --> 00:51:40,334
the Nonsan Persimmon-Strawberry Pastry,
made with strawberry and dried persimmon.

887
00:51:41,274 --> 00:51:43,841
The strawberries go well with the cream,

888
00:51:43,841 --> 00:51:46,941
and since dried persimmons go well
with cream cheese,

889
00:51:47,308 --> 00:51:53,374
I tried to connect the two fruit flavors
with Chantilly cream.

890
00:51:53,674 --> 00:51:55,408
In addition, I thought adding...

891
00:51:55,841 --> 00:52:00,674
roasted Kadayıf noodles
and pistachio paste...

892
00:52:00,699 --> 00:52:05,833
would add a fun texture to the pastry.

893
00:52:16,741 --> 00:52:20,141
(Hye Sung's Persimmon-Strawberry Pastry
that suffered a grueling process)

894
00:52:34,274 --> 00:52:39,208
First, I think you've won
in terms of cuteness.

895
00:52:39,874 --> 00:52:44,141
When it comes to expansion,

896
00:52:44,141 --> 00:52:47,974
I think it's definitely possible.

897
00:52:50,441 --> 00:52:53,608
But since it's very small,

898
00:52:54,441 --> 00:52:58,374
I think it's lacking
when it comes to portioning.

899
00:53:00,841 --> 00:53:04,308
When you first put in the kadayıf,

900
00:53:04,808 --> 00:53:06,708
you only mixed it with pistachio paste...

901
00:53:06,708 --> 00:53:09,074
and not chocolate, right?

902
00:53:09,841 --> 00:53:12,374
Right, I didn't.

903
00:53:12,374 --> 00:53:14,808
If you don't coat the inside,

904
00:53:14,808 --> 00:53:17,541
the kadayıf absorbs the moisture,

905
00:53:17,541 --> 00:53:19,974
so they've become very soggy.

906
00:53:20,341 --> 00:53:22,474
And regarding the cake,

907
00:53:22,474 --> 00:53:24,941
a roll cake needs to be soft,

908
00:53:24,941 --> 00:53:26,574
but many parts of it are broken.

909
00:53:27,241 --> 00:53:29,241
Looking at it overall,

910
00:53:31,441 --> 00:53:36,208
I don't think you presented the cake well,
which was disappointing.

911
00:53:36,208 --> 00:53:39,408
But for a bakery chef,
making a dessert couldn't have been easy.

912
00:53:39,408 --> 00:53:40,541
Well done.

913
00:53:44,141 --> 00:53:46,174
When I look at you,

914
00:53:46,174 --> 00:53:48,808
I can imagine
what the viewers are thinking.

915
00:53:49,574 --> 00:53:53,674
Many may think,
"How did she make it this far?"

916
00:53:54,174 --> 00:53:58,808
Others may think, "She may reduce
the credibility of this show."

917
00:54:01,908 --> 00:54:05,308
But in my opinion, I believe you are
more than capable...

918
00:54:05,308 --> 00:54:08,208
of making it to the next round.

919
00:54:08,708 --> 00:54:10,674
I think you have a well-developed palate.

920
00:54:10,674 --> 00:54:13,174
The balance of flavors is well done.

921
00:54:20,841 --> 00:54:23,741
Well, me being on this show itself,

922
00:54:23,741 --> 00:54:24,951
may reduce...

923
00:54:26,650 --> 00:54:29,808
the credibility of this show,

924
00:54:30,474 --> 00:54:32,774
and I have been thinking
the same of myself.

925
00:54:37,908 --> 00:54:38,741
So...

926
00:54:39,408 --> 00:54:43,141
(She struggles to get her words out.)

927
00:54:47,208 --> 00:54:50,608
I'm thankful to have made it this far.

928
00:54:54,574 --> 00:54:56,441
As I foray into this new arena,

929
00:54:56,441 --> 00:54:59,908
I was able to practice a lot
in a short time.

930
00:54:59,908 --> 00:55:02,341
And I believe this was an opportunity
for me to grow.

931
00:55:03,841 --> 00:55:04,841
Thank you.

932
00:55:07,141 --> 00:55:10,908
I'm just an ordinary consumer
with no technical skills.

933
00:55:10,908 --> 00:55:14,473
But you always capture
consumers' hearts...

934
00:55:14,497 --> 00:55:16,341
with your pastries,

935
00:55:16,341 --> 00:55:18,308
and I have enjoyed them every time.

936
00:55:18,741 --> 00:55:19,641
Don't cry.

937
00:55:20,274 --> 00:55:21,241
Thank you.

938
00:55:23,708 --> 00:55:26,708
(She showed her sincerity
for pastry-making.)

939
00:55:30,074 --> 00:55:32,074
Please show her results.

940
00:55:33,374 --> 00:55:36,308
(The News Anchor Who Bakes,
Lee Hye Sung, 401 points)

941
00:55:36,308 --> 00:55:39,974
Hye Sung, you received
a total of 401 points.

942
00:55:41,974 --> 00:55:44,608
(Top 7 Ranking: 5th Lee Hye Sung)

943
00:55:44,608 --> 00:55:46,641
You're in fifth place.

944
00:55:48,274 --> 00:55:50,341
I was feeling a mix of emotions.

945
00:55:50,908 --> 00:55:52,574
What a shame.

946
00:55:53,941 --> 00:55:55,808
There are...

947
00:55:57,108 --> 00:55:58,074
five contestants left.

948
00:56:00,141 --> 00:56:02,708
Let's see how the standings will
continue to change.

949
00:56:04,408 --> 00:56:06,908
Next up is Min Su.

950
00:56:07,408 --> 00:56:10,674
The pastry I present to you today is...

951
00:56:11,767 --> 00:56:15,411
a Geoje yuzu crepe noodle dish using
Geoje yuzus.

952
00:56:15,435 --> 00:56:17,967
The Geoje Yuzu Crepe Noodle Duo.

953
00:56:18,241 --> 00:56:19,841
- That's the name?
- Yes.

954
00:56:21,308 --> 00:56:23,141
I made crepes into noodles...

955
00:56:23,166 --> 00:56:26,299
to signify the waves in the ocean.

956
00:56:27,041 --> 00:56:32,374
I designed it in the shape of a sunrise
over the pebble beach.

957
00:56:36,274 --> 00:56:38,974
(Eating it like pasta drenched in sauce)

958
00:56:46,608 --> 00:56:48,074
It's really like pasta.

959
00:57:07,174 --> 00:57:09,241
Mimi, what do you think?

960
00:57:10,908 --> 00:57:13,441
The yuzu was great.

961
00:57:13,441 --> 00:57:16,741
I tried the noodles by themselves...

962
00:57:16,741 --> 00:57:19,441
and by rolling them up with the sauce.

963
00:57:19,441 --> 00:57:20,641
That was pretty fun.

964
00:57:20,641 --> 00:57:23,574
I think that part was great,

965
00:57:23,574 --> 00:57:25,141
but what was lacking for me was...

966
00:57:25,441 --> 00:57:27,014
fresh flavor of the yuzu.

967
00:57:27,038 --> 00:57:29,608
If it were more pronounced,

968
00:57:29,608 --> 00:57:31,908
or that flavor felt more fresh,

969
00:57:31,908 --> 00:57:33,774
it would've been more delicious
until the end.

970
00:57:33,774 --> 00:57:36,541
That part was a bit disappointing,

971
00:57:36,541 --> 00:57:37,541
but I enjoyed the dish.

972
00:57:39,608 --> 00:57:41,308
It seems there was a shift in perspective.

973
00:57:41,308 --> 00:57:44,341
Using crepes as noodles...

974
00:57:44,341 --> 00:57:48,474
and mixing them like this is
something I never thought of before.

975
00:57:48,474 --> 00:57:50,341
I think it was a great idea.

976
00:57:50,341 --> 00:57:51,896
You even used...

977
00:57:52,516 --> 00:57:55,174
the yuzu juice and zest.

978
00:57:55,174 --> 00:57:56,608
I can see the effort you put into this.

979
00:57:56,608 --> 00:58:00,874
But the thing you should have
used the most, you barely used.

980
00:58:00,874 --> 00:58:04,008
I looked at the confit you made here.

981
00:58:04,541 --> 00:58:06,441
You seem to make them really well.

982
00:58:07,274 --> 00:58:11,441
If you had finely sliced the confit
and mixed it in here,

983
00:58:12,041 --> 00:58:14,741
I think it would've
greatly elevated the flavor.

984
00:58:15,708 --> 00:58:21,108
Actually, I should've sliced
the confit and added it in,

985
00:58:21,441 --> 00:58:24,374
but I only had about 3 minutes left,

986
00:58:25,074 --> 00:58:26,374
so I couldn't add it.

987
00:58:26,374 --> 00:58:28,941
I was only able to place it on top.

988
00:58:33,641 --> 00:58:39,408
How many points will
the sixth challenger, Min Su, get,

989
00:58:41,008 --> 00:58:42,774
landing him in what place?

990
00:58:46,941 --> 00:58:49,574
(Cannoli Prince, Seong Min Su, 443 points)

991
00:58:49,574 --> 00:58:53,174
You received a total of 443 points.

992
00:58:53,741 --> 00:58:57,674
(Cannoli Prince, Seong Min Su, 443 points)

993
00:58:57,674 --> 00:59:01,274
You received a total of 443 points.

994
00:59:02,174 --> 00:59:04,174
(Top 7 Ranking: 3rd Seong Min Su)

995
00:59:04,174 --> 00:59:08,841
Min Su is now in third place.

996
00:59:10,008 --> 00:59:10,908
Thank you.

997
00:59:19,508 --> 00:59:20,574
I felt amazing.

998
00:59:24,241 --> 00:59:27,674
Next is Crazy Patissiere, Hwang Ji Oh.

999
00:59:28,774 --> 00:59:30,908
Icheon is famous for rice.

1000
00:59:31,183 --> 00:59:33,583
I made a round shape
and attached this on top.

1001
00:59:33,608 --> 00:59:34,874
(Making a pottery shape with the dough)

1002
00:59:41,208 --> 00:59:42,141
(Adding fresh cornelian cherry)

1003
00:59:42,141 --> 00:59:45,308
I thought that pairing them would
give it a unique flavor.

1004
00:59:46,574 --> 00:59:50,341
(A pastry reminiscent of Icheon pottery)

1005
00:59:53,308 --> 00:59:56,508
I prepared the Icheon's Tasty Duo.

1006
00:59:58,074 --> 01:00:01,274
For the filling, I roasted rice...

1007
01:00:01,274 --> 01:00:04,208
and made scorched rice cream.

1008
01:00:04,208 --> 01:00:07,374
I also used Icheon's regional specialty,
cornelian cherry,

1009
01:00:07,374 --> 01:00:10,508
to make a refreshing jam.

1010
01:00:11,441 --> 01:00:14,541
- It looks amazing.
- It's so pretty.

1011
01:00:18,508 --> 01:00:19,689
Should I lay something out?

1012
01:00:23,174 --> 01:00:26,374
Did you make the stamp yourself?

1013
01:00:26,374 --> 01:00:27,241
Yes.

1014
01:00:27,266 --> 01:00:29,799
I designed and made it myself.

1015
01:00:30,374 --> 01:00:32,241
- It's beautiful.
- Thank you.

1016
01:00:33,074 --> 01:00:34,341
I feel bad eating it.

1017
01:00:35,176 --> 01:00:36,477
It's too pretty to eat.

1018
01:00:53,386 --> 01:00:55,462
Ji Oh, I've been observing you,

1019
01:00:55,462 --> 01:00:57,331
and you're the type to grow
with every round.

1020
01:00:57,932 --> 01:00:59,996
Your improvement is very clear...

1021
01:01:00,534 --> 01:01:03,238
with every round.

1022
01:01:03,238 --> 01:01:07,270
In particular,
the dessert you prepared today...

1023
01:01:07,574 --> 01:01:11,111
was the best one I've had from you
this whole time.

1024
01:01:11,111 --> 01:01:13,008
It was also a great idea.

1025
01:01:13,080 --> 01:01:15,316
Your dessert today really surprised me.

1026
01:01:15,316 --> 01:01:17,313
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1027
01:01:18,419 --> 01:01:20,383
Let me talk quickly
so I can get back to eating.

1028
01:01:21,187 --> 01:01:22,885
It tastes wonderful.

1029
01:01:23,691 --> 01:01:26,727
If this dessert can't represent
this region,

1030
01:01:26,727 --> 01:01:29,063
what dessert can?

1031
01:01:29,063 --> 01:01:32,634
This is the best pastry
to represent Icheon rice.

1032
01:01:32,634 --> 01:01:34,467
I do not doubt that.

1033
01:01:34,467 --> 01:01:38,405
I'd drive 5 or 6 hours
just to get these buns.

1034
01:01:38,405 --> 01:01:39,540
Thank you for the wonderful dessert.

1035
01:01:39,540 --> 01:01:40,803
Thank you.

1036
01:01:42,209 --> 01:01:46,242
You only got here
from the redemption round last time.

1037
01:01:46,480 --> 01:01:48,816
I've been at the brink of elimination...

1038
01:01:48,816 --> 01:01:52,319
more often than anyone here.

1039
01:01:52,319 --> 01:01:54,217
And I've actually been eliminated.

1040
01:01:54,421 --> 01:01:56,252
So,

1041
01:02:00,891 --> 01:02:03,626
I'd like to take Gyeong Mu's place.

1042
01:02:04,565 --> 01:02:08,035
(She's going for first place.)

1043
01:02:08,836 --> 01:02:10,671
- Right on!
- That's the spirit!

1044
01:02:11,705 --> 01:02:13,040
That's our Ji Oh.

1045
01:02:13,040 --> 01:02:15,242
Thanks for keeping me on my toes.

1046
01:02:15,242 --> 01:02:16,277
You're welcome.

1047
01:02:17,637 --> 01:02:19,914
Better the devil you know, right?

1048
01:02:21,210 --> 01:02:22,870
I'd like to keep my devil,
that is, my first place.

1049
01:02:22,950 --> 01:02:24,347
- You want to stay there.
- Yes.

1050
01:02:26,086 --> 01:02:30,090
Will she manage...

1051
01:02:30,725 --> 01:02:32,922
to take Gyeong Mu's spot?

1052
01:02:34,348 --> 01:02:38,328
Please show...

1053
01:02:39,468 --> 01:02:40,768
Ji Oh's score!

1054
01:02:48,742 --> 01:02:51,045
(Surprised)

1055
01:02:54,982 --> 01:02:58,953
(Crazy Patissiere, Hwang Ji Oh,
568 points)

1056
01:03:00,120 --> 01:03:03,424
(Ji Oh received 568 points.)

1057
01:03:03,424 --> 01:03:04,591
Thank you.

1058
01:03:08,662 --> 01:03:10,397
(Top Seven Rankings)

1059
01:03:10,397 --> 01:03:12,166
(Ji Oh is in first place.)

1060
01:03:12,166 --> 01:03:13,335
Gyeong Mu,

1061
01:03:13,335 --> 01:03:16,532
please leave your seat for Ji Oh. Sorry.

1062
01:03:25,145 --> 01:03:26,380
She's at the top.

1063
01:03:27,215 --> 01:03:31,585
There's been a big shift
in the rankings...

1064
01:03:31,585 --> 01:03:35,318
with the announcement of Ji Oh's score.

1065
01:03:36,491 --> 01:03:39,927
However, unfortunately,

1066
01:03:39,927 --> 01:03:42,625
we'll start eliminating people
from this point on.

1067
01:03:43,832 --> 01:03:45,433
Hye Sung,

1068
01:03:45,433 --> 01:03:47,497
how do you feel right now?

1069
01:03:48,938 --> 01:03:53,903
I want to stay in the seventh spot
until the end.

1070
01:03:55,844 --> 01:03:58,012
She's honest, right?

1071
01:03:58,580 --> 01:04:00,814
The next person is...

1072
01:04:01,583 --> 01:04:04,251
Edison of the Baking World, Kwak Dong Uk.

1073
01:04:04,520 --> 01:04:06,220
Please step up to the stage.

1074
01:04:06,220 --> 01:04:08,422
(The eighth contestant in the semifinals,
Kwak Dong Uk)

1075
01:04:19,467 --> 01:04:21,268
(His specialty ingredient is
pollack from Inje.)

1076
01:04:21,268 --> 01:04:23,704
It was a fun experience
to work with pollack.

1077
01:04:24,271 --> 01:04:26,807
I thought dried pollack looked...

1078
01:04:27,074 --> 01:04:29,376
similar to kadayıf,

1079
01:04:29,643 --> 01:04:33,747
so I made a Turkish dessert called
Kunafa using them.

1080
01:04:36,817 --> 01:04:39,754
I mixed the flavors of pollack
with cheese...

1081
01:04:39,754 --> 01:04:41,255
to create a harmonious flavor.

1082
01:04:41,890 --> 01:04:44,759
(How does the pollack Kunafa taste?)

1083
01:04:47,028 --> 01:04:48,662
(Pollack Kunafa)

1084
01:04:49,660 --> 01:04:53,229
(A harmonious blend
of savory pollack and cheese)

1085
01:04:53,902 --> 01:04:56,403
Why don't we dig in, then?

1086
01:05:09,350 --> 01:05:10,851
I've never been more nervous.

1087
01:05:11,752 --> 01:05:14,722
This was our first time being evaluated
in front of everyone.

1088
01:05:26,266 --> 01:05:28,437
I commend your ideas...

1089
01:05:28,437 --> 01:05:31,300
and courage to challenge yourself
all the time.

1090
01:05:31,873 --> 01:05:32,973
Thank you.

1091
01:05:33,208 --> 01:05:36,973
The most important thing was
to feature the specialty item,

1092
01:05:37,444 --> 01:05:41,448
but I forgot that this had pollack
for a while.

1093
01:05:41,448 --> 01:05:44,585
The pollack is very underwhelming here.

1094
01:05:46,155 --> 01:05:49,819
It doesn't have
much of the pollack flavor,

1095
01:05:49,891 --> 01:05:53,594
and the mix
of the kadayıf and the cheese...

1096
01:05:53,861 --> 01:05:57,298
made it taste very confusing.

1097
01:05:57,392 --> 01:05:59,867
It doesn't taste like pollack,
but not cream cheese either.

1098
01:05:59,867 --> 01:06:01,869
And I can't taste the subtle nuttiness
of the kadayıf either.

1099
01:06:03,137 --> 01:06:05,935
It's lacking in many senses.

1100
01:06:06,274 --> 01:06:07,341
Thank you.

1101
01:06:08,042 --> 01:06:10,377
I only focused on making sure...

1102
01:06:10,377 --> 01:06:11,880
that it didn't taste
too much like pollack.

1103
01:06:11,880 --> 01:06:14,248
I forgot to think
about how to make it stand out.

1104
01:06:14,248 --> 01:06:16,746
That led to my failure.

1105
01:06:17,418 --> 01:06:20,454
There was a problem...

1106
01:06:20,856 --> 01:06:22,656
every step of the way today.

1107
01:06:22,656 --> 01:06:27,227
Making the kadayıf took too long,

1108
01:06:27,962 --> 01:06:30,698
and the bottom of the Kunafa stuck
to the pan.

1109
01:06:30,698 --> 01:06:32,032
(The nightmare of a dessert stuck
to the pan)

1110
01:06:34,636 --> 01:06:37,371
I knew that I was doomed.

1111
01:06:40,575 --> 01:06:44,578
That's all from the Masters.

1112
01:06:44,578 --> 01:06:47,082
There will be someone eliminated...

1113
01:06:47,083 --> 01:06:49,311
every time the results are announced.

1114
01:06:50,317 --> 01:06:54,154
Hye Sung, who's currently seventh,

1115
01:06:54,154 --> 01:06:56,023
received 401 points.

1116
01:06:57,959 --> 01:07:02,858
If Dong Uk gets more than 401 points,

1117
01:07:03,631 --> 01:07:06,300
Hye Sung will be eliminated by default.

1118
01:07:06,300 --> 01:07:08,369
You'll have to leave the factory.

1119
01:07:09,637 --> 01:07:13,741
Will Dong Uk,
the Edison of the Baking World,

1120
01:07:14,208 --> 01:07:19,008
beat Hye Sung with more than 401 points?

1121
01:07:20,114 --> 01:07:23,050
Please reveal...

1122
01:07:23,050 --> 01:07:24,509
(Time to change the lives
of the two contestants)

1123
01:07:31,928 --> 01:07:33,222
Dong Uk's score!

1124
01:07:33,827 --> 01:07:37,032
(Edison of the Baking World, Kwak Dong Uk,
394 points)

1125
01:07:37,032 --> 01:07:41,101
Dong Uk received 394 points, placing 8th.

1126
01:07:41,431 --> 01:07:43,004
(Edison of the Baking World, Kwak Dong Uk,
eliminated)

1127
01:07:43,004 --> 01:07:46,736
Unfortunately, you've been eliminated
in the semifinal mission.

1128
01:07:48,008 --> 01:07:49,912
(The first person to be eliminated
in the semifinals)

1129
01:07:49,912 --> 01:07:51,040
Oh, gosh.

1130
01:07:53,315 --> 01:07:55,945
Please give us a final comment.

1131
01:07:57,719 --> 01:08:01,021
I usually have to make products
that my company wants,

1132
01:08:01,021 --> 01:08:03,119
so I rarely get to make what I want.

1133
01:08:03,490 --> 01:08:05,693
But I got to do that here,

1134
01:08:05,693 --> 01:08:08,028
so it was a great experience. Thank you.

1135
01:08:12,599 --> 01:08:13,834
As heartbreaking as it is,

1136
01:08:14,501 --> 01:08:16,203
my goal was to be in the top ten...

1137
01:08:16,203 --> 01:08:19,074
when I initially signed up for the show.

1138
01:08:19,099 --> 01:08:20,566
And I reached exactly that far.

1139
01:08:22,876 --> 01:08:24,612
Unfortunately,
this is where it ends for me,

1140
01:08:24,612 --> 01:08:25,647
but I had fun.

1141
01:08:27,381 --> 01:08:29,683
There are two contestants to go,

1142
01:08:30,050 --> 01:08:34,750
and Kyung Joo and Hye Sung are
on the brink of elimination.

1143
01:08:35,522 --> 01:08:38,454
The next contestant may enter.

1144
01:08:39,193 --> 01:08:43,831
(The ninth contestant in the semifinals,
Kim Si Yeop)

1145
01:08:48,268 --> 01:08:50,405
Goyang is known...

1146
01:08:50,405 --> 01:08:53,641
for concerts and big exhibitions.

1147
01:08:54,108 --> 01:08:55,576
So, I prepared a pastry...

1148
01:08:55,576 --> 01:08:57,978
that can be easily eaten
while enjoying a concert.

1149
01:08:57,978 --> 01:08:59,079
(Goyang Gawaji Rice Dogs)

1150
01:08:59,380 --> 01:09:02,916
First, I used the sticky texture
of the Gawaji rice...

1151
01:09:02,916 --> 01:09:04,652
to make rice cake bars.

1152
01:09:04,652 --> 01:09:06,886
(He topped them with cheese,)

1153
01:09:07,955 --> 01:09:10,457
(then deep-fried the Gawaji rice kernels,)

1154
01:09:11,626 --> 01:09:12,726
(and coated the dogs with them.)

1155
01:09:12,726 --> 01:09:15,062
It has crispy fried rice on the outside.

1156
01:09:19,200 --> 01:09:23,237
I also added Korean beef
and young summer radish...

1157
01:09:23,237 --> 01:09:24,772
to make tteokgalbi.

1158
01:09:25,606 --> 01:09:28,542
You had to use the same ingredient...

1159
01:09:28,542 --> 01:09:31,712
as Ji Oh, who's currently in the lead.

1160
01:09:32,213 --> 01:09:35,811
Do you think you'll receive
better feedback than she did?

1161
01:09:36,951 --> 01:09:40,254
I'm a bit worried,

1162
01:09:40,254 --> 01:09:43,424
as Ji Oh made such a crazy piece,

1163
01:09:43,424 --> 01:09:44,558
but I'll do my best.

1164
01:09:45,793 --> 01:09:47,795
Shall we dig in?

1165
01:09:54,535 --> 01:09:56,437
Original, Cheongyang pepper, and seafood.

1166
01:09:56,736 --> 01:09:58,472
(Original, Cheongyang, and seafood)

1167
01:09:59,606 --> 01:10:00,663
(Original, Cheongyang, and seafood)

1168
01:10:00,688 --> 01:10:01,775
I'll start with the original.

1169
01:10:03,644 --> 01:10:06,380
(Starting with the original flavor)

1170
01:10:19,426 --> 01:10:20,494
Oh, gosh.

1171
01:10:27,401 --> 01:10:30,837
(Master Kwon is frowning.)

1172
01:10:32,307 --> 01:10:36,372
I love the idea of rice dogs.

1173
01:10:36,646 --> 01:10:39,486
It felt like eating rice burgers.

1174
01:10:40,414 --> 01:10:43,055
There were so many other ingredients...

1175
01:10:43,521 --> 01:10:48,147
that they distracted me from the rice.

1176
01:10:48,148 --> 01:10:51,426
Especially the seafood was very fishy.

1177
01:10:51,427 --> 01:10:53,099
(The seafood was quite fishy.)

1178
01:10:57,485 --> 01:11:02,609
It would've been better
if you had focused on one idea.

1179
01:11:03,310 --> 01:11:04,310
Thank you.

1180
01:11:05,384 --> 01:11:09,710
The original
and the Cheongyang pepper were perfect.

1181
01:11:11,516 --> 01:11:14,454
But even when I was watching you cook,

1182
01:11:14,982 --> 01:11:17,991
I wondered why you were using seafood.

1183
01:11:18,534 --> 01:11:21,947
Goyang doesn't have much to do
with the ocean.

1184
01:11:22,726 --> 01:11:27,886
Not surprisingly, the shrimp
and squid tasted very fishy.

1185
01:11:28,293 --> 01:11:29,607
That could've been better.

1186
01:11:30,173 --> 01:11:34,703
But it stayed focused on rice,
so I enjoyed it.

1187
01:11:35,155 --> 01:11:36,155
Thank you.

1188
01:11:37,196 --> 01:11:42,248
That's it for the Masters' feedback.
Depending on Si Yeop's score,

1189
01:11:42,482 --> 01:11:45,655
Hye Sung could be eliminated,

1190
01:11:46,141 --> 01:11:49,656
and Kyung Joo could be at risk as well.

1191
01:11:53,267 --> 01:11:57,030
Si Yeop's score will determine
the three contestants' fates.

1192
01:11:58,679 --> 01:12:01,845
Then, let's check...

1193
01:12:03,965 --> 01:12:05,671
his score now.

1194
01:12:08,622 --> 01:12:10,877
Who will be eliminated?

1195
01:12:14,981 --> 01:12:17,350
(Jeju Blue Ribbon Winner, Kim Si Yeop,
454 points)

1196
01:12:17,517 --> 01:12:19,853
(Kim Si Yeop, 454 points)

1197
01:12:22,286 --> 01:12:23,286
(Sighing)

1198
01:12:25,945 --> 01:12:29,828
Si Yeop takes fourth place.

1199
01:12:31,518 --> 01:12:33,800
When I prepare pastries,

1200
01:12:34,071 --> 01:12:36,669
I taste it after an hour.

1201
01:12:37,049 --> 01:12:41,016
I'll try to make pastries that taste
good even after a few hours.

1202
01:12:43,284 --> 01:12:47,868
Hye Sung worked so hard, so I know
she must feel really disappointed.

1203
01:12:47,869 --> 01:12:49,869
Thanks for all your hard work.

1204
01:12:51,242 --> 01:12:53,153
Thank you.

1205
01:12:54,313 --> 01:12:58,157
Si Yeop, please move to the Pass Zone.

1206
01:13:06,283 --> 01:13:11,002
I've been thinking about how my life will
change from here.

1207
01:13:11,769 --> 01:13:14,142
I realized I was more serious...

1208
01:13:14,615 --> 01:13:16,276
about pastries than I thought.

1209
01:13:17,296 --> 01:13:21,481
I can't imagine what I'd be doing
if I hadn't done this.

1210
01:13:23,975 --> 01:13:25,218
He's the last contestant.

1211
01:13:27,354 --> 01:13:28,755
This must be killing his nerves.

1212
01:13:31,290 --> 01:13:36,662
As Si Yeop came in fourth,

1213
01:13:37,705 --> 01:13:39,372
the rankings have changed.

1214
01:13:40,478 --> 01:13:42,478
Depending on the next contestant's score,

1215
01:13:42,837 --> 01:13:46,939
Kyung Joo could be eliminated.

1216
01:13:48,154 --> 01:13:53,076
I'll hold on to hope and stay positive.

1217
01:13:53,762 --> 01:13:58,057
Last contestant, Pastry Idol,
Ju Yeong Seok,

1218
01:13:58,081 --> 01:13:59,445
please come to the judge's table.

1219
01:13:59,446 --> 01:14:01,487
(Semifinals: last contestant,
Ju Yeong Seok)

1220
01:14:07,970 --> 01:14:11,898
I thought about what kind of pastry
to make to represent Gumi.

1221
01:14:12,417 --> 01:14:16,102
Gumi is known for its flour, grapes,
and melons.

1222
01:14:17,642 --> 01:14:21,907
I made these langue de chat cookies
using only flour from Gumi.

1223
01:14:22,801 --> 01:14:27,046
I wanted to reflect Gumi
and add the Gumi style to it.

1224
01:14:27,934 --> 01:14:32,646
So I came up with the idea
of making gummies as a pun.

1225
01:14:33,286 --> 01:14:34,988
(The grape and melon gummies are
the key feature.)

1226
01:14:36,155 --> 01:14:39,091
(Three types of Gumi Langue de Chat)

1227
01:14:41,427 --> 01:14:45,698
(How do the langue de chat cookies taste
with Gumi's ingredients?)

1228
01:14:55,275 --> 01:14:56,842
Aren't the gummies too chewy?

1229
01:15:08,254 --> 01:15:09,956
(Tilting his head)

1230
01:15:13,812 --> 01:15:14,812
This is hard.

1231
01:15:17,078 --> 01:15:19,332
The gummies you made with wine.

1232
01:15:20,023 --> 01:15:23,615
When making these gummies,
did you use gelatin or pectin?

1233
01:15:24,124 --> 01:15:27,383
The texture wasn't good enough
with just pectin,

1234
01:15:27,384 --> 01:15:30,343
so I used pectin and added some gelatin.

1235
01:15:31,303 --> 01:15:36,149
The gummies are too chewy for my taste.

1236
01:15:38,164 --> 01:15:42,724
I wanted to play it safe for this round,

1237
01:15:42,749 --> 01:15:45,825
so I added more gelatin
to exaggerate the texture.

1238
01:15:47,360 --> 01:15:49,295
If you had put it in the fridge,
it would have been even tougher.

1239
01:15:50,739 --> 01:15:51,739
I'm sorry.

1240
01:15:53,919 --> 01:15:59,509
For me, the buttercream stood out
more than the gummies.

1241
01:15:59,995 --> 01:16:02,108
The langue de chat was...

1242
01:16:02,576 --> 01:16:06,210
more impressive.
I wish the gummies were...

1243
01:16:06,417 --> 01:16:08,417
thicker or had a stronger flavor.

1244
01:16:08,643 --> 01:16:13,029
That would've made it more special.

1245
01:16:13,662 --> 01:16:16,095
But I could really taste the flour...

1246
01:16:16,701 --> 01:16:20,880
in the langue de chat, which I loved.

1247
01:16:21,347 --> 01:16:22,347
Thank you.

1248
01:16:25,573 --> 01:16:28,534
Now, his score from the Masters...

1249
01:16:28,866 --> 01:16:31,299
will decide the top seven.

1250
01:16:32,192 --> 01:16:36,375
Will Yeong Seok make the top seven,

1251
01:16:36,884 --> 01:16:40,179
or will Kyung Joo remain in seventh place?

1252
01:16:40,851 --> 01:16:43,215
Before I reveal his score,

1253
01:16:43,970 --> 01:16:47,653
let me tell you the difference
between their scores.

1254
01:16:49,509 --> 01:16:50,509
It's only two points.

1255
01:16:50,510 --> 01:16:52,358
(The difference is only two points.)

1256
01:16:53,048 --> 01:16:54,048
Only two points?

1257
01:16:55,608 --> 01:17:00,733
Those two points decided their fate.

1258
01:17:01,667 --> 01:17:02,667
Who do you think will win?

1259
01:17:05,672 --> 01:17:11,643
Which contestant made
the top 7 by only 2 points?

1260
01:17:12,665 --> 01:17:16,944
One will advance to the finals,
and one will leave the factory.

1261
01:17:17,845 --> 01:17:20,653
Time to reveal the score.

1262
01:17:22,490 --> 01:17:23,490
Let's reveal the score!

1263
01:17:25,091 --> 01:17:26,704
(Pastry Idol, Ju Yeong Seok, 415 points)

1264
01:17:26,705 --> 01:17:27,705
Let's reveal the score!

1265
01:17:31,609 --> 01:17:35,568
Ju Yeong Seok's total is 415 points.

1266
01:17:37,403 --> 01:17:39,472
(Seventh place,
Pastry Idol, Ju Yeong Seok)

1267
01:17:39,705 --> 01:17:42,934
(Ju Yeong Seok, seventh place,
Jang Kyung Joo, eliminated)

1268
01:17:42,935 --> 01:17:43,935
All right.

1269
01:17:44,988 --> 01:17:49,014
You've made the top seven.
Congratulations.

1270
01:17:49,672 --> 01:17:52,718
Thank you.
I'll learn from my mistakes here...

1271
01:17:52,989 --> 01:17:58,691
and do better in the next round.
Thank you again.

1272
01:17:59,845 --> 01:18:03,262
It's a shame,
but I gave it my all in every round...

1273
01:18:03,511 --> 01:18:05,511
and have no regrets.

1274
01:18:05,771 --> 01:18:09,669
I'll leave this show without any regrets.

1275
01:18:10,237 --> 01:18:12,837
Thank you.

1276
01:18:13,087 --> 01:18:14,087
Great work.

1277
01:18:14,488 --> 01:18:16,575
- Good work.
- Thank you.

1278
01:18:19,265 --> 01:18:21,046
- Thank you.
- Well done.

1279
01:18:24,458 --> 01:18:27,698
- I'm sorry.
- Don't be. Congratulations. Good luck.

1280
01:18:35,194 --> 01:18:38,497
(The person in seventh place changed
at the end.)

1281
01:18:43,382 --> 01:18:45,315
I knew I could do better
in the next round...

1282
01:18:45,481 --> 01:18:48,674
and I have more to show.
I wish I could keep going.

1283
01:18:50,010 --> 01:18:54,130
But I'm so proud of myself
for making it this far.

1284
01:19:00,456 --> 01:19:03,723
The journey to find the ultimate pastry
that will take over the world.

1285
01:19:05,781 --> 01:19:10,035
Through four fierce competitions,
they proved themselves...

1286
01:19:10,798 --> 01:19:13,798
and made it into the top seven.

1287
01:19:14,702 --> 01:19:15,702
Let me introduce them.

1288
01:19:15,703 --> 01:19:17,336
(Here are the top seven
of "Bake Your Dream.")

1289
01:19:20,916 --> 01:19:22,356
First place in the semifinals.

1290
01:19:24,909 --> 01:19:27,747
She turns her ideas into reality
with her hands.

1291
01:19:28,668 --> 01:19:29,781
Crazy Patissiere,

1292
01:19:31,720 --> 01:19:32,880
Hwang Ji Oh.

1293
01:19:35,280 --> 01:19:37,512
Now that I've made it to the finals,
I don't want to lose.

1294
01:19:40,502 --> 01:19:42,060
Second place in the semifinals.

1295
01:19:43,816 --> 01:19:46,176
He dominates every moment...

1296
01:19:47,182 --> 01:19:48,634
with his world-class, proven skills.

1297
01:19:50,478 --> 01:19:53,005
Dessert Macho, Lee Gyeong Mu.

1298
01:19:54,585 --> 01:19:57,009
I'm getting more and more determined
to win.

1299
01:20:00,164 --> 01:20:01,714
Third place in the semifinals.

1300
01:20:04,263 --> 01:20:07,720
He has grown
with youthful ambition and passion.

1301
01:20:09,162 --> 01:20:12,391
Bukhansan Summit Bakery, Kim Jin Seo.

1302
01:20:13,668 --> 01:20:17,230
Fourth place in the semifinals.
He's a passionate, hands-on baker.

1303
01:20:18,493 --> 01:20:21,767
Jeju Blue Ribbon Winner, Kim Si Yeop.

1304
01:20:24,632 --> 01:20:29,174
He's the smart one. He's experienced,
quick, and full of great ideas.

1305
01:20:32,138 --> 01:20:33,138
Fifth place in the semifinals.

1306
01:20:35,637 --> 01:20:37,082
With creative recipes,

1307
01:20:38,511 --> 01:20:40,520
he stretches the boundaries of dessert.

1308
01:20:42,323 --> 01:20:45,257
Cannoli Prince, Seong Min Su.

1309
01:20:47,008 --> 01:20:49,408
I'll win first place
and take the prize money.

1310
01:20:53,141 --> 01:20:55,974
A pastry chef with 26 years of experience.

1311
01:20:58,774 --> 01:21:01,974
Fine-Dining Patissier, Yoon Hwa Young.

1312
01:21:05,094 --> 01:21:06,855
He has a chef's mindset,

1313
01:21:07,841 --> 01:21:10,841
so he's excellent
at interpreting his dishes.

1314
01:21:14,241 --> 01:21:16,208
From a K-pop singer to a pastry chef.

1315
01:21:16,208 --> 01:21:17,241
(Seventh place in the semifinals)

1316
01:21:18,074 --> 01:21:21,108
Pastry Idol, Ju Yeong Seok.

1317
01:21:23,708 --> 01:21:26,021
He always throws a quiet but big blow.

1318
01:21:26,208 --> 01:21:28,141
That's the scariest kind of person.

1319
01:21:30,108 --> 01:21:33,128
I want to be validated as a pastry chef.

1320
01:21:35,741 --> 01:21:38,441
(The top seven contestants
of "Bake Your Dream")

1321
01:21:38,441 --> 01:21:39,674
Let's go!

1322
01:21:45,841 --> 01:21:48,674
Everyone is extra serious today
since this is the finals.

1323
01:21:50,741 --> 01:21:55,308
We'll now explain
how the final round will go.

1324
01:21:56,274 --> 01:21:59,408
There will be two rounds in the finals.

1325
01:22:00,908 --> 01:22:04,174
The final winner will be chosen...

1326
01:22:04,174 --> 01:22:06,808
based on the combined scores
from Rounds 1 and 2.

1327
01:22:09,674 --> 01:22:12,808
For Round One...

1328
01:22:14,474 --> 01:22:15,274
of the finals,

1329
01:22:22,141 --> 01:22:23,745
you'll make "Baked Goods for a Meal."

1330
01:22:25,841 --> 01:22:26,841
"Baked Goods for a Meal."

1331
01:22:28,274 --> 01:22:32,108
You'll collaborate with chefs
from different cuisines...

1332
01:22:32,674 --> 01:22:37,041
to create a pastry
that's good enough as a meal.

1333
01:22:38,941 --> 01:22:41,174
My goal in the first round
of the finals is...

1334
01:22:41,741 --> 01:22:42,541
to place first.

1335
01:22:44,474 --> 01:22:47,208
Baking with food? That's a bit much.

1336
01:22:49,008 --> 01:22:50,074
I can win first place.

1337
01:22:52,808 --> 01:22:55,008
(Finals Round One,
"Baked Goods for a Meal")

1338
01:22:55,008 --> 01:22:56,741
For the first round of the finals,

1339
01:22:57,308 --> 01:22:58,674
you're making "Baked Goods for a Meal."

1340
01:22:59,274 --> 01:23:02,874
We will now reveal the chefs collaborating
with the seven contestants.

1341
01:23:12,708 --> 01:23:15,641
(Chinese: Hwang Ji Oh and Hwang Jin Seon)

1342
01:23:16,474 --> 01:23:18,874
One of the top Chinese cuisine chefs
in Korea,

1343
01:23:18,874 --> 01:23:21,041
Chef Hwang Jin Seon.

1344
01:23:23,674 --> 01:23:25,341
China has a rich culinary culture.

1345
01:23:25,341 --> 01:23:27,541
Its cuisine offers many inspirations
for something new.

1346
01:23:30,141 --> 01:23:33,308
Gyeong Mu will be collaborating...

1347
01:23:34,241 --> 01:23:36,741
with the 16th Master Artisan
in Culinary Arts in Korea,

1348
01:23:36,741 --> 01:23:38,308
who's a master in Japanese cuisine.

1349
01:23:38,308 --> 01:23:40,174
It's Chef Ahn Yu Seong.

1350
01:23:41,974 --> 01:23:45,841
Flavors used in Japanese cuisine aren't
too bold.

1351
01:23:46,141 --> 01:23:49,974
I chose Japanese cuisine,
as I wanted to incorporate the subtlety.

1352
01:23:51,541 --> 01:23:54,141
(Thailand: Kim Jin Seo and Kim Yoo Ah)

1353
01:23:55,341 --> 01:23:57,541
She's a chef certified
by the Thai royal family.

1354
01:23:59,308 --> 01:24:00,841
She's one of the leaders
in Thai cuisine in Korea.

1355
01:24:01,274 --> 01:24:03,508
It's Chef Kim Yoo Ah.

1356
01:24:05,141 --> 01:24:06,974
I chose Thai food...

1357
01:24:06,974 --> 01:24:08,808
because I wanted to use...

1358
01:24:08,808 --> 01:24:11,741
its spicy recipes and vibrant spices.

1359
01:24:13,041 --> 01:24:15,308
(French: Kim Si Yeop and Lee Seung Jun)

1360
01:24:15,508 --> 01:24:18,108
A chef who works with elements from nature
in his cooking.

1361
01:24:18,108 --> 01:24:20,241
An artist in French dining,

1362
01:24:20,608 --> 01:24:22,608
Chef Lee Seung Jun.

1363
01:24:23,741 --> 01:24:25,808
I'm familiar with French food,

1364
01:24:25,808 --> 01:24:28,074
so I'm ready to create something
never seen before...

1365
01:24:28,074 --> 01:24:30,608
by combining French cuisine with baking.

1366
01:24:31,974 --> 01:24:33,774
(Korean: Seong Min Su and Lee Won Il)

1367
01:24:34,008 --> 01:24:35,408
Korea's favorite chef,

1368
01:24:35,674 --> 01:24:37,341
who not only cooks Korean food...

1369
01:24:37,341 --> 01:24:40,641
but also bakes incredibly well,
Chef Lee Won Il.

1370
01:24:41,774 --> 01:24:44,974
I chose Korean cuisine...

1371
01:24:44,974 --> 01:24:46,541
because it has a lot to work with...

1372
01:24:46,541 --> 01:24:48,508
to create new recipes.

1373
01:24:49,549 --> 01:24:51,983
(French: Yoon Hwa Young and Oh Se Deuk)

1374
01:24:52,008 --> 01:24:54,474
A master French chef of 26 years,

1375
01:24:55,241 --> 01:24:56,574
Oh Se Deuk.

1376
01:24:57,641 --> 01:25:00,441
I had to choose French
because I love French cuisine.

1377
01:25:00,808 --> 01:25:02,441
I'm sure we'll be great together.

1378
01:25:03,408 --> 01:25:05,641
(Korean: Ju Yeong Seok and Cho Seo Hyeong)

1379
01:25:06,174 --> 01:25:08,108
The prodigy of fusion Korean food
in Euljiro,

1380
01:25:08,674 --> 01:25:10,008
Cho Seo Hyeong.

1381
01:25:11,441 --> 01:25:14,441
She's great at using seasonal ingredients,

1382
01:25:14,441 --> 01:25:16,274
so I have faith
that we can make great things together.

1383
01:25:17,683 --> 01:25:19,149
(The pairs for the first round
of the finals,)

1384
01:25:19,174 --> 01:25:23,274
("Baked Goods for a Meal")

1385
01:25:28,208 --> 01:25:29,041
The finals...

1386
01:25:31,608 --> 01:25:34,574
have now begun.

1387
01:25:35,608 --> 01:25:36,974
In the first round of the finals,

1388
01:25:37,541 --> 01:25:39,541
you'll have to create baked goods...

1389
01:25:39,541 --> 01:25:41,408
that stand out
as the main course in a meal...

1390
01:25:41,408 --> 01:25:43,941
instead of a dessert.

1391
01:25:45,908 --> 01:25:47,474
Don't forget the theme.

1392
01:25:48,174 --> 01:25:50,941
The baked goods have to be the star.

1393
01:25:53,841 --> 01:25:58,074
We have a special Master joining us.

1394
01:25:58,741 --> 01:26:01,674
Please welcome
the world-class CEO, Park Jeong Eun.

1395
01:26:03,874 --> 01:26:06,674
("Atomix, the Korean Restaurant in NYC,
Named the Best in North America")

1396
01:26:06,908 --> 01:26:08,974
(Raising the reputation of Korean food...)

1397
01:26:08,974 --> 01:26:10,641
(at the heart of the fine-dining scene
in New York)

1398
01:26:11,641 --> 01:26:15,708
Hello, I'm Park Jeong Eun,
the CEO of atomix in New York.

1399
01:26:15,708 --> 01:26:19,474
As I'm sitting as the judge
for "Baked Goods for a Meal,"

1400
01:26:19,474 --> 01:26:22,508
I'll pay close attention...

1401
01:26:22,508 --> 01:26:24,841
to how the food goes with the baked goods.

1402
01:26:27,174 --> 01:26:29,441
It's time to hear from each contestant...

1403
01:26:29,441 --> 01:26:31,208
before we get started.

1404
01:26:31,541 --> 01:26:34,474
I don't want to leave this center spot.

1405
01:26:34,474 --> 01:26:36,041
I'll win first place.

1406
01:26:36,041 --> 01:26:37,341
I've come so far,

1407
01:26:37,341 --> 01:26:39,141
so I might as well strive to be first.

1408
01:26:39,141 --> 01:26:40,808
I'll be the final champion.

1409
01:26:41,074 --> 01:26:44,508
We've been cooking French food
for 50 years combined.

1410
01:26:44,508 --> 01:26:46,674
We'll make a baked good
that can't be found anywhere.

1411
01:26:47,108 --> 01:26:48,441
You'll see a one-of-a-kind product.

1412
01:26:51,041 --> 01:26:52,408
- I'm excited.
- That was so cool.

1413
01:26:53,974 --> 01:26:57,341
You get 200 minutes.

1414
01:26:57,341 --> 01:26:58,341
Just 200 minutes?

1415
01:26:59,408 --> 01:27:00,374
That's about three hours.

1416
01:27:01,341 --> 01:27:03,941
The culinary chefs can only participate...

1417
01:27:03,941 --> 01:27:06,374
in the last 100 minutes.

1418
01:27:08,341 --> 01:27:09,541
Before we begin the round,

1419
01:27:10,074 --> 01:27:13,008
culinary chefs, please move to your seats.

1420
01:27:13,441 --> 01:27:14,674
Wait.

1421
01:27:18,574 --> 01:27:21,608
Wait. We have something to say.

1422
01:27:22,274 --> 01:27:23,241
Go ahead.

1423
01:27:24,108 --> 01:27:27,708
Can I work with the chef
in the first 100 minutes instead?

1424
01:27:29,141 --> 01:27:32,541
Are you trying to use the food he cooks
as a filling?

1425
01:27:32,541 --> 01:27:36,508
Yes, I'd like to stuff my dough
and bake with his food.

1426
01:27:36,508 --> 01:27:39,241
If I can cook in the first 100 minutes,

1427
01:27:39,241 --> 01:27:41,141
I won't cook in the next 100.

1428
01:27:41,874 --> 01:27:43,741
That sounds fair, right?

1429
01:27:44,208 --> 01:27:46,274
- Is everyone okay with that?
- Yes, we are.

1430
01:27:46,641 --> 01:27:48,536
Contestants, are you okay with that?

1431
01:27:48,808 --> 01:27:49,674
- Yes.
- Yes.

1432
01:27:49,674 --> 01:27:51,874
- Yes.
- Thank you.

1433
01:27:51,874 --> 01:27:54,941
All six chefs, except Won Il,

1434
01:27:54,941 --> 01:27:57,108
please move to your seats.

1435
01:27:57,708 --> 01:28:00,308
- We know we'll win, anyway.
- Okay.

1436
01:28:00,308 --> 01:28:01,608
(Wishing the contestants the best)

1437
01:28:01,608 --> 01:28:02,674
- Good luck.
- Thank you.

1438
01:28:03,574 --> 01:28:05,174
- See you later.
- Cheers!

1439
01:28:09,008 --> 01:28:13,708
We will now begin the first round
of the finals.

1440
01:28:14,774 --> 01:28:15,841
Bake Your Dream.

1441
01:28:16,108 --> 01:28:19,108
Please show us your dream
through your baking.

1442
01:28:21,974 --> 01:28:23,708
- Good luck!
- Let's go!

1443
01:28:23,708 --> 01:28:24,741
It's begun!

1444
01:28:24,741 --> 01:28:26,607
(Round One of the finals,
"Baked Goods for a Meal," begins.)

1445
01:28:26,908 --> 01:28:29,574
- Let's go!
- You can do it!

1446
01:28:29,574 --> 01:28:32,041
(The contestants are
starting their projects.)

1447
01:28:49,441 --> 01:28:51,841
(Min Su and Won Il are working together.)

1448
01:28:51,841 --> 01:28:53,808
The setup is much different...

1449
01:28:53,808 --> 01:28:55,574
now that we have chefs cooking too.

1450
01:28:56,541 --> 01:28:58,808
- There are stoves.
- And a lot more tools.

1451
01:28:58,808 --> 01:29:01,041
We don't use those tools in baking.

1452
01:29:02,041 --> 01:29:04,574
This is a great mission for the finals.

1453
01:29:04,574 --> 01:29:06,141
- It's different.
- Yes.

1454
01:29:07,208 --> 01:29:08,341
It's so different.

1455
01:29:09,074 --> 01:29:11,774
They're a team,
but they're doing such different things.

1456
01:29:11,774 --> 01:29:13,941
(What are they baking
as "Baked Goods for a Meal?")

1457
01:29:14,374 --> 01:29:18,208
Hwa Young is using a roller.

1458
01:29:18,208 --> 01:29:19,074
A pie roller.

1459
01:29:19,074 --> 01:29:21,208
(Hwa Young is working with a pie roller.)

1460
01:29:22,108 --> 01:29:24,108
They're both fine-dining chefs.

1461
01:29:24,108 --> 01:29:25,241
- Yes, they are.
- Right.

1462
01:29:25,241 --> 01:29:26,508
- And French chefs.
- Indeed.

1463
01:29:27,241 --> 01:29:28,174
They're also the same age.

1464
01:29:29,041 --> 01:29:30,408
- Their synergy...
- They've been cooking...

1465
01:29:30,408 --> 01:29:32,008
- For half a century combined.
- Half a century.

1466
01:29:32,508 --> 01:29:36,308
The mission is basically made
for Hwa Young.

1467
01:29:36,308 --> 01:29:38,141
Just like how Koreans eat side dishes
with rice,

1468
01:29:38,141 --> 01:29:42,341
- you always have bread with French food.
- On the side.

1469
01:29:42,874 --> 01:29:46,041
- "Half a century" sounds intimidating.
- For sure.

1470
01:29:46,041 --> 01:29:47,537
("French Baked Goods for a Meal"
by French chefs)

1471
01:29:47,908 --> 01:29:49,708
I took the completely wrong direction...

1472
01:29:49,974 --> 01:29:53,574
for the semifinal mission.

1473
01:29:54,408 --> 01:29:57,908
(They had to bake with local ingredients
in Round Four.)

1474
01:30:00,608 --> 01:30:04,508
(His pastries didn't feature
the special ingredient enough.)

1475
01:30:05,441 --> 01:30:06,874
(As a result,)

1476
01:30:08,241 --> 01:30:10,774
(other contestants kept beating him,)

1477
01:30:11,641 --> 01:30:13,674
(and he barely made it to the finals
in sixth place.)

1478
01:30:13,941 --> 01:30:16,008
I was so ashamed of myself after that.

1479
01:30:16,008 --> 01:30:20,174
This time, I'll use that as a lesson...

1480
01:30:20,174 --> 01:30:22,841
and throw a fastball.

1481
01:30:23,374 --> 01:30:26,074
I bet Hwa Young will do an amazing job
this round.

1482
01:30:26,074 --> 01:30:27,708
- I agree.
- Yes.

1483
01:30:27,708 --> 01:30:28,641
I wonder what he'll make.

1484
01:30:29,308 --> 01:30:31,774
We're baking...

1485
01:30:31,774 --> 01:30:34,068
Lobster vol-au-vent...

1486
01:30:34,541 --> 01:30:36,074
with in-season black truffles.

1487
01:30:36,544 --> 01:30:38,873
It's the ultimate luxury.

1488
01:30:39,117 --> 01:30:42,017
Back in medieval and early modern France,

1489
01:30:42,017 --> 01:30:43,685
it was considered a luxury dish.

1490
01:30:43,685 --> 01:30:45,886
Even now, it's still served...

1491
01:30:46,087 --> 01:30:49,523
at major events at the Elysee Palace.

1492
01:30:49,858 --> 01:30:52,027
I also chose it...

1493
01:30:52,027 --> 01:30:55,396
since it suits the mission with a chef.

1494
01:31:01,036 --> 01:31:02,797
He added something to the dough.

1495
01:31:02,971 --> 01:31:04,204
Isn't that a truffle?

1496
01:31:04,505 --> 01:31:06,239
Since it's French, it must be a truffle.

1497
01:31:06,239 --> 01:31:07,875
- It looks like a truffle.
- Truffle.

1498
01:31:07,875 --> 01:31:09,570
- It must be a truffle.
- Since it's French.

1499
01:31:09,710 --> 01:31:11,812
Do they use truffles a lot in France?

1500
01:31:11,812 --> 01:31:12,747
In this season...

1501
01:31:12,747 --> 01:31:16,483
White truffles come into season in autumn,

1502
01:31:16,852 --> 01:31:19,320
- and in winter...
- Black truffles.

1503
01:31:19,320 --> 01:31:21,288
- it's black truffles.
- In winter, most fine dining places...

1504
01:31:21,288 --> 01:31:23,350
in France have truffle courses.

1505
01:31:23,351 --> 01:31:24,513
(Even winter truffle courses in France)

1506
01:31:30,658 --> 01:31:34,435
(Cutting the truffle dough into circles)

1507
01:31:40,341 --> 01:31:41,743
(Hwa Young is stacking the dough.)

1508
01:31:41,743 --> 01:31:42,910
- What is that?
- What is that?

1509
01:31:43,311 --> 01:31:44,445
That's cute.

1510
01:31:48,192 --> 01:31:50,427
He's stacking the dough...

1511
01:31:50,452 --> 01:31:53,188
so it rises like a tart shell.

1512
01:31:53,188 --> 01:31:54,722
- It's feuilletage dough.
- Will it rise like this?

1513
01:31:54,722 --> 01:31:56,156
Yes, it'll puff up like this.

1514
01:31:56,225 --> 01:31:58,527
The important thing is
that it rises evenly.

1515
01:31:58,527 --> 01:32:00,395
It can be lopsided like this.

1516
01:32:00,395 --> 01:32:02,564
You should give it enough resting time,

1517
01:32:02,564 --> 01:32:04,733
so it doesn't come out crooked.

1518
01:32:04,733 --> 01:32:07,101
It's all about how it puffs up
into the shape.

1519
01:32:07,101 --> 01:32:08,168
(Will he have enough time?)

1520
01:32:08,602 --> 01:32:10,631
That puff pastry is key.

1521
01:32:14,475 --> 01:32:15,809
I prepared 12 lobsters.

1522
01:32:15,809 --> 01:32:16,911
(There are 12 lobsters.)

1523
01:32:16,911 --> 01:32:19,179
Will he use that many live lobsters?

1524
01:32:19,179 --> 01:32:20,508
This is too much.

1525
01:32:20,948 --> 01:32:22,649
He's intimidating us with the ingredient.

1526
01:32:22,649 --> 01:32:23,684
It's the finals.

1527
01:32:24,585 --> 01:32:27,114
He wants to go all out at the end.

1528
01:32:27,989 --> 01:32:30,124
This really feels like a final.

1529
01:32:30,124 --> 01:32:32,259
Isn't that a bit much?

1530
01:32:32,993 --> 01:32:34,962
- It can't go wrong.
- This can't turn out wrong.

1531
01:32:34,962 --> 01:32:35,996
This can't taste bad.

1532
01:32:42,803 --> 01:32:44,705
Hwa Young is going to give everything
he's got today.

1533
01:32:44,705 --> 01:32:45,806
Totally.

1534
01:32:45,806 --> 01:32:48,142
- It looks like he's going all in.
- I know.

1535
01:32:48,142 --> 01:32:50,477
He had a close call last time,

1536
01:32:51,345 --> 01:32:52,346
so I'm looking forward to this.

1537
01:32:52,346 --> 01:32:53,914
It's like he's saying,

1538
01:32:53,914 --> 01:32:55,816
"This is Yoon Hwa Young."

1539
01:32:58,385 --> 01:33:00,921
(After prepping 12 lobsters,)

1540
01:33:01,956 --> 01:33:04,525
(here are the black truffles.)

1541
01:33:06,527 --> 01:33:08,362
- They're truffles.
- Hwa Young took out the truffles.

1542
01:33:08,387 --> 01:33:09,922
They went all out on ingredients.

1543
01:33:10,664 --> 01:33:11,866
Lobster and truffles.

1544
01:33:12,441 --> 01:33:13,676
That's so French.

1545
01:33:13,701 --> 01:33:17,605
Truffles are not often used in baking.

1546
01:33:17,605 --> 01:33:19,373
This suits his nickname.

1547
01:33:19,373 --> 01:33:21,808
He's the Fine-Dining Patissier.

1548
01:33:21,808 --> 01:33:24,946
He seems to be making something
very fine-dining-esque.

1549
01:33:24,946 --> 01:33:26,480
You don't have to hold back.
It's the finals.

1550
01:33:27,915 --> 01:33:29,416
He's basically cheating.

1551
01:33:29,416 --> 01:33:31,719
Seasonal ingredient, truffles.

1552
01:33:32,219 --> 01:33:36,357
Lobster and truffles are
classic ingredients in France.

1553
01:33:36,357 --> 01:33:39,960
They're often served at important meals.

1554
01:33:40,461 --> 01:33:43,230
So I think it makes sense
to use them at this stage.

1555
01:33:43,797 --> 01:33:45,766
Using expensive ingredients...

1556
01:33:45,766 --> 01:33:47,835
raises expectations,

1557
01:33:47,835 --> 01:33:50,170
so you can't make this...

1558
01:33:51,372 --> 01:33:52,373
taste bad.

1559
01:33:54,174 --> 01:33:57,872
(Will he live up
to everyone's expectations?)

1560
01:33:58,579 --> 01:34:00,147
I'm worried about the Japanese one.

1561
01:34:00,147 --> 01:34:01,849
I have a sense
of what the other cuisines will be like.

1562
01:34:01,849 --> 01:34:03,750
I can imagine poo phat pong curry,

1563
01:34:03,750 --> 01:34:05,012
but a Japanese pastry is...

1564
01:34:06,153 --> 01:34:07,354
(She's worried about Gyeong Mu.)

1565
01:34:07,354 --> 01:34:09,917
The country I picked
for "Baked Goods for a Meal"...

1566
01:34:10,424 --> 01:34:11,592
is Japan.

1567
01:34:12,194 --> 01:34:13,517
Where's Gamae Japanese Restaurant?

1568
01:34:13,517 --> 01:34:15,028
- In Gwangju.
- In Gwangju.

1569
01:34:15,028 --> 01:34:16,429
It's still the best in Gwangju.

1570
01:34:16,429 --> 01:34:17,398
He rules Gwangju.

1571
01:34:17,398 --> 01:34:20,261
- Really?
- He has an entire street.

1572
01:34:21,602 --> 01:34:22,826
He's so popular in Gwangju.

1573
01:34:22,851 --> 01:34:23,971
(Chef Ahn is a top chef from Gwangju.)

1574
01:34:24,738 --> 01:34:26,307
- How are you?
- Hello.

1575
01:34:26,307 --> 01:34:27,341
Hello.

1576
01:34:27,942 --> 01:34:31,312
I thought about presenting the pastry
in an assorted sushi style,

1577
01:34:31,312 --> 01:34:35,383
so I tried making shari bread with rice.

1578
01:34:35,383 --> 01:34:38,552
- So you shaped the bread like shari?
- Yes.

1579
01:34:38,552 --> 01:34:40,788
I tried making...

1580
01:34:40,788 --> 01:34:43,824
one hundred percent gluten-free
rice bread,

1581
01:34:43,824 --> 01:34:46,120
which also looks like shari.

1582
01:34:46,827 --> 01:34:49,436
Please check the texture for me.

1583
01:34:49,461 --> 01:34:50,725
(Sushi bread evaluated by a master chef)

1584
01:34:54,101 --> 01:34:55,903
- It's nice.
- Is it doable?

1585
01:34:57,384 --> 01:34:58,986
I'm totally blown away.

1586
01:34:59,473 --> 01:35:00,875
How is this possible?

1587
01:35:01,976 --> 01:35:04,678
(His idea shocked the master.)

1588
01:35:07,478 --> 01:35:10,183
I wanted to keep the rice bread
as moist as possible,

1589
01:35:10,183 --> 01:35:12,553
so I used the starch from the grains.

1590
01:35:13,152 --> 01:35:15,490
I added as much water as possible...

1591
01:35:15,490 --> 01:35:16,657
when mixing the dough.

1592
01:35:21,295 --> 01:35:24,625
There are lots of other Japanese dishes,

1593
01:35:24,699 --> 01:35:25,967
but he picked sushi.

1594
01:35:25,967 --> 01:35:27,628
- I know.
- It's an interesting choice.

1595
01:35:27,801 --> 01:35:29,230
Japanese cuisine actually has
a lot of bread.

1596
01:35:35,075 --> 01:35:36,343
(Gyeong Mu is shaping the dough
into shari.)

1597
01:35:36,343 --> 01:35:37,778
He's shaping them into shari.

1598
01:35:37,778 --> 01:35:38,979
The rice used for sushi.

1599
01:35:45,186 --> 01:35:47,755
- I'm scared.
- Can the bread replace rice?

1600
01:35:48,689 --> 01:35:51,158
He's really gambling.

1601
01:35:51,692 --> 01:35:53,621
I don't even eat rice when I eat sushi.

1602
01:35:53,994 --> 01:35:56,498
Pardon? Do you only eat the fish?

1603
01:35:56,498 --> 01:35:57,732
That's sashimi, then.

1604
01:35:57,732 --> 01:35:58,934
Yes. I only eat half the rice.

1605
01:35:58,934 --> 01:36:01,234
That's perfect for Mimi then,

1606
01:36:01,234 --> 01:36:02,503
- Right.
- since you prefer bread to rice.

1607
01:36:02,503 --> 01:36:05,299
- It's perfect.
- But with fish?

1608
01:36:08,910 --> 01:36:11,979
Yu Seong's team is making small balls...

1609
01:36:11,979 --> 01:36:13,013
like yullan.

1610
01:36:13,148 --> 01:36:14,850
To make it look like sushi.

1611
01:36:14,850 --> 01:36:16,310
How many grains of rice are there?

1612
01:36:17,965 --> 01:36:20,567
He's using the molds to make
the sushi shapes uniform.

1613
01:36:26,401 --> 01:36:27,701
- That one.
- Sushi bread.

1614
01:36:27,728 --> 01:36:28,963
I can't wait to check out the shari.

1615
01:36:29,629 --> 01:36:30,597
Bread shari.

1616
01:36:30,597 --> 01:36:32,166
- The rice!
- The shari is done.

1617
01:36:32,166 --> 01:36:33,267
The shari is out.

1618
01:36:35,970 --> 01:36:37,071
(The shari bread is done.)

1619
01:36:37,071 --> 01:36:38,305
They actually look like rice.

1620
01:36:38,305 --> 01:36:39,773
- It looks the same.
- Right?

1621
01:36:40,107 --> 01:36:41,709
It must have a fun texture.

1622
01:36:41,709 --> 01:36:43,812
You bite into it, and it's chewy.

1623
01:36:43,812 --> 01:36:48,683
I hope he doesn't put fish on that.

1624
01:36:48,683 --> 01:36:54,321
He's not going to put raw fish
on top of that, right?

1625
01:36:54,321 --> 01:36:55,554
I think he is.

1626
01:36:55,554 --> 01:36:57,391
- Really?
- I think so.

1627
01:36:57,890 --> 01:36:59,054
That's why I'm scared.

1628
01:36:59,660 --> 01:37:01,117
(How will their "Baked Goods
for a Meal" turn out?)

1629
01:37:01,142 --> 01:37:02,223
This is driving me crazy.

1630
01:37:04,031 --> 01:37:05,266
Master!

1631
01:37:06,021 --> 01:37:07,001
(A fish filleting show?)

1632
01:37:07,635 --> 01:37:09,971
(The top chefs
in the culinary world are here.)

1633
01:37:10,237 --> 01:37:11,361
(Plenty to see)

1634
01:37:11,361 --> 01:37:13,439
(Plenty to enjoy)

1635
01:37:13,439 --> 01:37:15,368
(Plenty to eat)

1636
01:37:15,743 --> 01:37:18,138
(A completely different level
of presentation from baking)

1637
01:37:19,013 --> 01:37:21,171
This is not a cooking competition.

1638
01:37:21,171 --> 01:37:23,284
(They have to make baked goods
for a meal.)

1639
01:37:23,684 --> 01:37:24,818
- Oh, dear.
- That looks good.

1640
01:37:24,818 --> 01:37:26,085
That looks delicious.

1641
01:37:26,085 --> 01:37:28,422
The pastry should be the main thing,
with food as the side.

1642
01:37:28,656 --> 01:37:30,881
(Bread that works as a meal)

1643
01:37:30,881 --> 01:37:34,518
(The main focus is still bread.)

1644
01:37:34,518 --> 01:37:37,524
(Make the best baked goods for a meal.)

1645
01:37:37,631 --> 01:37:40,767
(However)

1646
01:37:41,268 --> 01:37:45,071
(The plan goes off track.)

1647
01:37:45,573 --> 01:37:48,631
(Something unexpected comes up.)

1648
01:37:48,631 --> 01:37:49,844
Just ten seconds.

1649
01:37:50,077 --> 01:37:51,304
Isn't it a bit too salty?

1650
01:37:51,305 --> 01:37:52,877
No, it'll be fine. Is it really salty?

1651
01:37:52,878 --> 01:37:53,914
It's salty.

1652
01:37:53,914 --> 01:37:55,108
It was a disaster.

1653
01:37:55,108 --> 01:37:56,808
(Broken teamwork)

1654
01:37:57,218 --> 01:37:58,352
(A tough journey...)

1655
01:37:58,352 --> 01:38:00,955
(to the final victory)

1656
01:38:00,955 --> 01:38:02,723
I'm here to win.

1657
01:38:03,216 --> 01:38:05,559
I don't want to be ashamed of myself.

1658
01:38:05,588 --> 01:38:07,962
(A high-stakes battle
over "Baked Goods for a Meal")

1659
01:38:07,962 --> 01:38:10,631
(Who will win this battle?)

1660
01:38:10,631 --> 01:38:12,181
(Bake Your Dream)
